  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"ahri","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Ahri","Ahri","Ahri","Ahri"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your level 3 all-in with Q into E-tangle out-trades her single-target poke, so pressure the first three levels before her waveclear comes online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ahri's level 6 flips the lane: three Spirit Rush dashes let her step over your Tangle-Barbs and dodge your telegraphed Pop Blossom, so respect her mobility once she hits 6."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Luden's/Malignance and boots she chunks you with a full Charm-Q-passive rotation before you close the gap, and her mobility means your R rarely lands clean."},{"when":"Late","text":"At two items Ahri kites your immobile approach with Spirit Rush, waits out your R, then Charms you mid-cast; you need flanks and disguise to make ult land."}],"wants":{"you":["Bushes and fog to hide your true model and land an unreactable disguised Q-E","A jungler to collapse before she buys mobility so you cash the level 3-5 lead","Short trades where your P-empowered Q and E burst beats her single Charm"],"foe":["Open space to chain her three Spirit Rush dashes and reset distance","Baiting your Tangle-Barbs and Pop Blossom on cooldown, then Charming you naked","Sidelane and roam tempo where her ult mobility outclasses your immobility"]},"early":"You own the first three levels: Neeko's Q double-detonation plus a P-disguised auto out-trades Ahri's single-target Q poke, and her level 1-2 has no dash to escape your E root, so play forward and punish every Q she throws at the wave.","mid":"The lane inverts at 6. Ahri's Spirit Rush gives her three charges to dodge your Tangle-Barbs and step outside your Pop Blossom radius, and Charm now sets up a full burst combo you can't answer while she's mobile and you're not; trade only when her dashes are down.","late":"With items Ahri is a slippery, safe caster who kites your telegraphed all-in; your R needs a disguise flank or ally CC to connect, so group, hide your model, and force fights where she can't Spirit Rush away.","whys":["Neeko's Q-into-E burst and P auto out-trade Ahri's single-target level 1 poke.","At level 2 you still have no dash to fear and your empowered Q chunks her on the wave.","Your level 3 all-in with Q, E root and Shapesplitter beats her pre-6 kit.","Spirit Rush arrives and lets Ahri dodge your immobile Tangle-Barbs and step out of R range.","At 6 her three-dash mobility plus Charm burst overpowers your telegraphed ult.","First-item Ahri kites your approach and lands full Charm-Q rotations before you engage.","At two-plus items her sustained mobility and safe poke keep your immobile R off her entirely."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"akali","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Akali","Akali"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Akali is weak and mana-starved before her core items, so your level 3 Q-E all-in and constant wave shove keep her pinned under tower and off CS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Perfect Execution ult gives two dashes, but you have Pop Blossom too; hold R until she commits Shroud so your point-blank AoE and E root catch her mid-combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Akali finishes a component like Hextech Alternator plus boots she has the mana and burst to one-combo squishies through Twilight Shroud, so ward and buy an early seeker/spellshield."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Akali roams and assassinates from Shroud; your immobility makes you a target, so play with vision, save E as a self-peel, and disguise to dodge her opener."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove her under tower levels 1-5 while she's mana-starved to deny CS and XP","Bait her Twilight Shroud early, then E-root and Q her out of it","Hold Pop Blossom for when she dashes in so your AoE stun answers her all-in"],"foe":["Scaling to her first-item mana pool so she can spam Q and combo you","Roaming with Shroud stealth to snowball other lanes off your immobility","Picking you as an easy immobile target once she can burst through your HP"]},"early":"You dominate the opening: Akali is mana-hungry and squishy pre-6, so use your superior Q waveclear and level 3 Q-E all-in to shove her in and zone her off the wave, punishing every time she steps up to last-hit.","mid":"You stay ahead into the mid-game. Her level 6 Perfect Execution is scary, but Neeko's own R plus Tangle-Barbs root lets you answer her dive; bait Twilight Shroud, root her as she reappears, and blow her up before she resets, keeping the lead you built early.","late":"Akali flips the matchup once itemized: full mana and burst let her combo you through Shroud and roam-assassinate, and your immobility makes you her ideal target; rely on vision, a defensive item, disguise openers, and E as a peel to survive her all-in windows.","whys":["Your Q waveclear and range beat mana-starved Akali on the level 1 wave.","At 2 you out-shove and out-trade her before she has combo mana.","Your level 3 Q-E all-in punishes her weak, itemless early state.","She still can't burst you through your HP, so your zoning lead holds.","At 6 your Pop Blossom and E root answer her Perfect Execution dive.","First-item mana and burst let Akali finally combo you through Twilight Shroud.","At two-plus items her roam-assassinate potential overwhelms your immobility."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"akshan","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Akshan wants to poke with Avengerous Q and dance on terrain with his Heroic Swing hook, but your Q-E all-in and faster wave shove punish him whenever he has no wall to swing off."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Comeuppance ult is a global execute more useful for picks than dueling you; keep the wave shoving so he can't freely channel it, and hold Pop Blossom for when he swings in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a first item Akshan's crit poke and Swing burst become a real skill-check duel; the trade hinges on whether you can E-root him off his grapple animation, so it's a genuine coinflip."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your AoE teamfight R and disguise flanks outscale his single-target pick kit, so group and force 5v5s where his reset-hunting matters less than your Pop Blossom."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove fast and deny him terrain to Heroic Swing off of","E-root him mid-grapple to cancel his Swing and land your Q burst","Teamfights where your AoE R beats his single-target pick pattern"],"foe":["Walls and camps to poke-and-dash with Heroic Swing safely","A first-item spike to out-duel you in a skill-based poke war","Sidelane isolation and reset-hunting with his Comeuppance execute"]},"early":"You control the early game: Akshan is a poke-and-reposition laner who needs walls to swing off, and Neeko's superior Q waveclear plus a level 3 Q-E all-in lets you shove him in and zone him whenever his Heroic Swing is on cooldown.","mid":"You keep the edge through levels 3-6, but stay alert at 6 when Comeuppance can snipe low allies elsewhere on the map; hold your R and E for when he grapples in, root him off the animation, and blow him up before he resets away.","late":"The first-item window is a true skill matchup, a poke duel decided by whether you land E on his Swing; past that your AoE teamfight ult and disguise flanks outscale his single-target pick kit, so group up and pull the game into 5v5s.","whys":["Your Q waveclear and lack of a needed wall beat his level 1 poke setup.","At 2 you out-shove and punish him whenever Heroic Swing is down.","Your level 3 Q-E all-in overpowers his fragile early duel.","Without a first item he can't out-trade your empowered combo yet.","At 6 your Pop Blossom and E answer his Swing dive while he holds ult for picks.","First-item Akshan's crit poke turns the duel into a skill-based coinflip.","At two-plus items your AoE R and flanks outscale his single-target pick kit."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"anivia","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Anivia","Anivia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Anivia is slow and mana-starved before her ult, with a telegraphed Flash Frost stun; dodge the Q, then run her down with your own Q-E all-in while she's low on mana and defenceless."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her level 6 Glacial Storm plus egg passive is a real turning point; you can still all-in through it, but her Rebirth means you must save Pop Blossom to burst her a second time after the egg."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Anivia lands a Lost Chapter and Tear she perma-shoves with R and walls off your engage; her Frostbite combo now chunks you, so trading through her zone gets punishing."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Anivia zones entire teamfights with Glacial Storm and her wall splits your engage; your telegraphed R struggles to reach her, so you need flanks and disguise to touch her."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Flash Frost, then all-in her mana-starved pre-6 form with Q-E","Kill her before Rebirth is up, or save R to burst the egg's re-form","All-in windows while her Glacial Storm and Crystallize are on cooldown"],"foe":["Reaching level 6 for Rebirth safety and permanent R waveclear","Lost Chapter and Tear mana to spam Frostbite combos and zone you","Teamfights where Glacial Storm and her wall split your immobile engage"]},"early":"You beat Anivia early: she's immobile, slow, and mana-hungry with a slow, dodgeable Flash Frost, so sidestep the Q stun and punish with your Q-E all-in and faster wave tempo before she has the mana or ult to defend herself.","mid":"The level 6 window is a skill check. Glacial Storm and the Rebirth egg give her survivability and waveclear, but you can still all-in through it if you respect the egg; save Pop Blossom and E to burst her a second time after Rebirth pops, or she'll simply re-form and reset the trade.","late":"Anivia takes over once itemized: with Tear and Lost Chapter she perma-shoves, walls off your approach with Crystallize, and zones fights with Glacial Storm while her egg negates your burst; your telegraphed R can't reach her, so rely on disguised flanks and ally CC to open her up.","whys":["You dodge her slow Flash Frost and out-trade her mana-starved level 1.","At 2 she's still immobile and defenceless against your Q poke and shove.","Your level 3 Q-E all-in beats her before Rebirth or R come online.","She remains squishy and mana-limited, so your all-in pressure holds.","At 6 Glacial Storm and the Rebirth egg make the all-in a genuine skill check.","First-item Tear and Lost Chapter let her perma-shove, wall, and Frostbite-chunk you.","At two-plus items her zone control and egg outscale your telegraphed immobile R."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"annie","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Annie","Annie","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Annie has her Pyromania stun stacked at level 4-5, every trade risks a free Q-W stun into burst; watch her passive charge counter and back off when she's at three stacks."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her level 6 Tibbers all-in with a stacked stun can one-shot you if you're caught; hold Flash and don't walk into her Q range while Pyromania is up, because your immobility offers no escape."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After her first item you out-range and out-poke her once her stun is spent; punish the cooldown window with Q and E, since she's defenceless for a few seconds after Tibbers."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your AoE teamfight R and disguise flanks outscale her single point-and-click stun, so bait Tibbers, survive it, then group and win the 5v5 with Pop Blossom."}],"wants":{"you":["Track her Pyromania stack counter and only trade when it's not full","Punish the window right after she spends her stun with Q-E poke","Teamfights where your AoE R outvalues her single-target Tibbers combo"],"foe":["A stacked Pyromania stun to open a free Q-W into full burst","Level 6 Tibbers all-in on your immobile, escape-less body","Short trades where her point-and-click stun beats your telegraphed kit"]},"early":"You start ahead: at levels 1-2 Annie hasn't stacked Pyromania yet, so her Q is just poke with no stun threat, and your faster Q waveclear plus E lets you shove and pressure her before her all-in comes online.","mid":"Annie takes over the mid-levels once her stun is up. From level 4 through 6 a full Pyromania charge means a free Molten Shield or Q into stun-burst, and at 6 a stacked Tibbers all-in can delete your immobile body; count her stacks, respect her range, and never trade into a full charge.","late":"The matchup swings back to you with items despite the tough middle: after she spends her stun she's defenceless on a long cooldown, so your superior range, Q-E poke, AoE Pop Blossom and disguise flanks let you punish those windows and outscale her single-target burst in teamfights.","whys":["At level 1 Annie has no stun stacked, so your Q poke and shove win out.","At 2 she still can't threaten a stun and you out-trade her range.","Your level 3 combo lands before her Pyromania charge is reliable.","A stacked stun at 4-5 gives Annie a free Q-W burst you can't escape.","Level 6 Tibbers with a full stun can one-shot your immobile body.","First-item you punish her long post-stun cooldown with superior poke.","At two-plus items your AoE R and flanks outscale her single-target stun."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"aurelionsol","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Aurelion Sol is a pure stacking scaler who wants to farm safely with his Breath of Light Q; your level 3 Q-E all-in punishes his weak, defenceless early and denies the stacks he needs."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Falling Star/Singularity ult gives a slow and a stun on the second cast, but it's short-range and he's still squishy; hold E to root him mid-channel and all-in with Pop Blossom."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Before he snowballs his stacks, your first-item burst combo blows him up in one E-Q rotation; keep shoving and denying him the farm his whole kit depends on."},{"when":"Late","text":"Aurelion Sol only becomes a threat if allowed to stack for free; keep punishing with disguise flanks and AoE R so he never reaches the scaling that would flip the lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny his Breath of Light stacks with constant shove and all-ins","E-root him during his ult channel and burst before he can react","End the game before his stacks scale by snowballing your early lead"],"foe":["Free, uninterrupted farm to stack Breath of Light unpunished","Reaching late scaling where his stacked Q and ult zone teamfights","Avoiding your all-ins so his fragile early survives to the scaling phase"]},"early":"You crush Aurelion Sol early: he's a defenceless stacker who just wants to farm with Breath of Light, so your Q waveclear and level 3 Q-E all-in let you shove him in, zone him off CS, and deny the stacks his entire kit is built around.","mid":"You stay firmly ahead through the mid-levels. His level 6 Singularity offers a slow and delayed stun, but it's short-range and he remains squishy, so root him with Tangle-Barbs mid-channel, drop Pop Blossom, and keep him too far behind on stacks to fight back.","late":"The only path back for Aurelion Sol is free scaling, and you don't give it: keep snowballing your early lead with disguise flanks and AoE Pop Blossom, deny his farm through every phase, and close the game before his stacks ever come online.","whys":["Your Q poke and shove beat his passive, farm-focused level 1.","At 2 he's still defenceless and you deny his early stacks.","Your level 3 Q-E all-in punishes his fragile, stack-hungry early.","He can't fight back while behind on stacks, so your lead grows.","At 6 your E root and Pop Blossom answer his short-range Singularity.","First-item burst blows up the still-unstacked Aurelion Sol in one combo.","At two-plus items your denial keeps him from ever reaching his scaling."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"aurora","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your level 3 Q-E all-in beats her early before her Twofold Movement passive and Q spirits ramp; press the first three levels while she's low on mana and can't kite you yet."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Aurora's Between Worlds ult creates a zone she can dash back into with W Across the Sanguine, so she dodges your telegraphed Pop Blossom; she flips the lane at 6 with her mobility."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a first item her W blink resets fights and her Q spirit poke chunks you before you engage; your immobile approach gets kited, so trades favour her."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Aurora's W dash and ult zone let her dodge your R and reposition; you need disguise flanks and ally CC to pin her before she blinks out."}],"wants":{"you":["Pressure levels 1-3 before her passive and mana let her kite","Land E-root when her W Across the Sanguine dash is on cooldown","Short all-ins while she lacks the items to reposition and poke safely"],"foe":["Her W blink and ult zone up to dodge your Tangle-Barbs and Pop Blossom","First-item spike to poke with Q spirits and reset fights with W","Open space where her mobility kites your immobile engage"]},"early":"You take the first three levels: before Aurora's Twofold Movement passive and Q spirit poke come online she's mana-limited and can't kite, so your Q waveclear and level 3 Q-E all-in let you shove and pressure her while she has no dash charged.","mid":"The lane flips once she hits her stride. Aurora's W Across the Sanguine dash and Between Worlds ult zone let her sidestep your telegraphed Tangle-Barbs and Pop Blossom, and her spirit poke starts to add up; from level 4 onward trade only when her W is down, because otherwise she blinks out of every all-in.","late":"Aurora stays ahead with items: her W reset and ult reposition kite your immobile approach while Q spirits chunk you before you close, and your telegraphed R rarely lands clean; rely on disguised flanks, fog, and ally CC to pin her before she dashes away.","whys":["Your Q poke and shove beat her mana-starved, kite-less level 1.","At 2 she still has no reliable dash and you out-trade her.","Your level 3 Q-E all-in punishes her before her passive and W ramp.","Her W Across the Sanguine dash starts dodging your telegraphed Tangle-Barbs.","At 6 her Between Worlds ult zone lets her sidestep your Pop Blossom.","First-item W resets and Q poke let Aurora kite your immobile engage.","At two-plus items her mobility and reposition keep your telegraphed R off her."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"azir","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Azir","Azir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your E-Q-W all-in beats his two-soldier setup; root through the soldier line and detonate the outer Q petals on top of him for a big chunk."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom out of a clone or bush is a faster, more reliable engage than his defensive E Shifting Sands into R; force the all-in now while it's yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Azir's Nashor's Tooth plus three soldiers flips lane control to him — expect to get poked and shoved under tower."},{"when":"Late","text":"His soldier DPS and R Emperor's Divide disengage outscale your burst; look for R flanks in fights instead of straight-lane duels."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade every time he steps up for a soldier last-hit","Land E Tangle-Barbs through the soldier line into your Q","All-in before he completes Nashor's Tooth"],"foe":["Farm safely at max soldier range with Q Conquering Sands","Shove and roam once his waveclear comes online","Reach three soldiers plus Nashor's to zone you off the wave"]},"early":"Azir is one of the weakest early laners in the game with only two soldiers and no reliable trade pattern, so you own levels 1-2 outright. Walk up and auto-harass whenever he steps to last-hit with a soldier, and punish any Q Conquering Sands he throws for a cannon by trading back with an empowered auto and Q Blooming Burst on his return. His only self-peel is E Shifting Sands, and pre-6 he rarely has the mana to both farm and shield. Keep the wave central so he can't safely use soldiers to push you under tower.","mid":"With E Tangle-Barbs unlocked you get a real all-in: root through his soldier line and layer the Q blossoms for a burst chunk before his E cooldown recovers. Azir wants to disrespect you at soldier range, so bait a soldier auto, then W Shapesplitter to close and drop Q on top of him where the outer petals detonate. Watch his mana — a good Azir will try to shove and roam, so ping and follow because his waveclear is slow until Nashor's. Your level 6 Pop Blossom is a cleaner engage than his defensive R, so every all-in window before his first item belongs to you.","late":"Once Azir finishes Nashor's Tooth and Blackfire Torch his soldier zoning flips the lane; three soldiers plus attack speed let him poke, waveclear instantly, and kite your Q. His R Emperor's Divide becomes a genuine disengage against your Pop Blossom, and he can shove you in and take grubs or drakes. From here play for teamfight flanks with your clone rather than dueling him in a straight lane, because his DPS and range outscale your burst.","whys":["Azir's two-soldier start gives him no trade pattern, so your auto-harass rules level 1.","You still out-trade with empowered autos while his mana forces a farm-or-shield choice.","Unlocking E Tangle-Barbs gives you an all-in his single E can't answer.","Your Q-blossom burst and root beat his fragile pre-item soldier setup.","Pop Blossom is a cleaner engage than Azir's defensive E-R, so the all-in favours you.","Nashor's plus three soldiers lets Azir poke, waveclear, and zone you off farm.","His soldier DPS and R Emperor's Divide disengage outrange and outscale your burst."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"brand","win":["Brand","Brand","Neeko","Brand","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 flank-root-Q is your one clean kill window before Brand out-pokes you again at levels 4-5."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even ult trade — your E into R Pop Blossom kills him, but his R Pyroclasm on a stun chain kills you; play the cooldowns."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Skill matchup: dodge his W Pillar of Flame and bait Q Sear with your clone before you commit."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both of you one-shot on a landed combo — roam and pick rather than face-check his poke on the way to objectives."}],"wants":{"you":["Spike at level 3 and flank-root before he re-scales","Bait his Q Sear stun with your W Shapesplitter clone","Dodge Pillar of Flame by hugging the melee minions"],"foe":["Poke you down with W Pillar at levels 1-2 and 4-5","Land Q Sear on an Ablaze target for the stun","Chain his full R Pyroclasm combo before you close distance"]},"early":"Brand out-ranges and out-pokes you at levels 1-2 with W Pillar of Flame, which he drops on the wave to zone you and chip you as you last-hit. His combo threatens your passive-less early HP bar, and if he lands Q Sear on a target that is already Ablaze he stuns you, so never walk into a Pillar with his Q up. Hug the melee minions to make his skillshots harder and give up a couple of CS rather than eating a Pillar of Flame. These first two levels belong to Brand's range advantage.","mid":"Level 3 is your spike — with E Tangle-Barbs and W Shapesplitter you can flank his skillshots, root him, and dump Q Blooming Burst for damage a squishy Brand can't survive without flash. But the window is narrow: at levels 4-5 he out-scales the trade again as his W and E Conflagration ranks let him poke you down before you reach him. Manage the wave so you're not caught in his AoE, and only commit when his Pillar of Flame is on cooldown. His stun combo stays the deciding factor, so bait it out with your clone first.","late":"Past first item the lane settles into a skill matchup — both of you carry real kill pressure, but neither dominates. Brand's R Pyroclasm and full combo can take you from 100 to 0 if he lands a chained stun, while your E-flash into R Pop Blossom does the same to him. Play around his Pillar and Sear cooldowns, use your clone to bait, and look to roam since both champs excel at picking off mispositioned targets. Warding to dodge his poke on the path to objectives is what tips these even fights your way.","whys":["Brand's W Pillar range lets him zone and chip you before you can retaliate.","His poke combo keeps out-trading your passive-less early bar.","Your level 3 E-root into Q burst spikes hard enough to kill a squishy Brand.","Ranked W and E Conflagration out-poke you again before you can reach him.","Both ults one-shot on a landed combo, so the level 6 trade is even.","Neither champ dominates post-item; it comes down to dodging Pillar and baiting Sear.","Equal pick potential means warding and cooldown-tracking, not raw stats, decide fights."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"cassiopeia","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 E-Q all-in is your last kill window before Cass ramps; take it while her W Miasma is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Petrifying Gaze stuns your face-up Q or dash engages — respect it or you die mid-combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Chained Q-W-E DoT out-damages your burst, and her Miasma grounds your escape."},{"when":"Late","text":"Pure Cassiopeia lane: farm safe and only engage in fights where a teammate can eat her R."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade with autos and Q at levels 1-2 before she ramps","All-in at level 3 while W Miasma is on cooldown","Avoid all face-up engages once her R is up"],"foe":["Farm with Q Noxious Blast and stack passive movement speed","Chain Q-W-E to ramp her Twin Fang damage","Ground you with Miasma and catch your engage with R Petrifying Gaze"]},"early":"Cassiopeia starts slow and weak — her Q Noxious Blast is her only early damage and she has almost no auto-attack range, so you win the early levels by walking up and trading with autos into Q Blooming Burst. She wants to farm with Q and stack her passive movement speed; deny that by threatening a trade every time she steps up. Levels 1-2 are cleanly yours as long as you don't stand in her Q for free damage.","mid":"Your level 3 is the last clean window before she comes online — E Tangle-Barbs into Q while her W Miasma is down lets you burst her, since she can't yet chain Twin Fangs efficiently. Force the all-in here. Once she has a couple of points in E Twin Fang and starts landing Q into the E ramp, the trades invert and she out-sustains and out-damages you. Her W Miasma grounds you, cutting off your W Shapesplitter escape and any flash-less disengage.","late":"From level 4 onward this is Cassiopeia's lane. With Q-W-E chained she does relentless poison damage you can't burst through, and her R Petrifying Gaze punishes your face-up engages — if you Q or dash straight at her, she stuns you mid-animation and kills you. Her Miasma zoning locks you out of the wave and off objectives. Play safe, farm side lanes, and only engage in fights where a teammate can body-block her R; a straight duel past first item is a loss.","whys":["Cass's slow, low-range start lets you out-trade with autos and Q.","She still lacks the ability chain to punish you, so early harass is yours.","Your level 3 E-Q all-in bursts her before Twin Fang ramps online.","Chained Q-W-E DoT and Miasma grounding invert the trades in her favour.","R Petrifying Gaze hard-punishes your face-up engages.","Her ramping poison out-damages your burst and zones you off the wave.","Sustained DoT plus R control make a straight duel unwinnable."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"diana","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Neeko","Diana","Diana"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 E-root out-bursts her pre-Lunar-Rush; trades even out at 4-5 around who lands their skillshot."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your instant Pop Blossom beats her telegraphed R Moonfall engage — hold R to counter her jump."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Diana's E-R all-in plus W shields tanks your burst and resets E onto you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Her shielded sustained damage out-trades your one combo; fight grouped, not in the side lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish every Q Crescent Strike she farms with","Root her at level 3 before Lunar Rush exists","Hold Pop Blossom to counter her R Moonfall jump"],"foe":["Farm safe with Q and stack her passive","All-in with E Lunar Rush into R once shields and items are online","Reset E Lunar Rush off a kill to snowball"]},"early":"Diana's early laning is passive — she farms with Q Crescent Strike and stacks her passive for waveclear, and pre-6 she has no gap-closer, so you dictate the first levels. Every time she throws Q to CS, step up and punish with an auto into Q Blooming Burst; she can't answer without eating a full trade. Her W Pale Cascade shield blunts one exchange, so trade after it's popped rather than into it. Levels 1-2 are yours.","mid":"At level 3 you keep the edge — E Tangle-Barbs roots her out of a Q hit for a burst window before her E Lunar Rush exists. Levels 4-5 even out: she gets Pale Cascade value and her Q-passive combo hurts, so trades become about who lands their skillshot. Level 6 swings back to you: your Pop Blossom is an instant point-blank AoE that beats her telegraphed R Moonfall engage, and if she E-R's onto you, a clone bait plus your R stun can turn it. Hold your ult for her jump rather than opening with it.","late":"Once Diana completes items her all-in overwhelms you — E Lunar Rush into R Moonfall pulls you in, her W shields tank your burst, and her reset E finishes the kill. Her sustained magic damage and shielding out-trade your single burst rotation past first item. Don't face-check her in the side lane; group with your team so her all-in gets punished by follow-up, and use your clone to make her commit R onto the wrong target.","whys":["Diana has no gap-closer pre-6, so you punish her Q farming freely.","She still can't answer your step-up trades without a dash.","Your E-root burst beats her before Lunar Rush comes online.","Pale Cascade value and Q-passive damage even the trades around skillshots.","Instant Pop Blossom counters her telegraphed R Moonfall engage.","Her E-R all-in with shields tanks your burst and resets onto you.","Shielded sustained damage out-trades your single burst rotation."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"ekko","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Neeko","Ekko","Ekko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 E-root beats his Phase Dive escape; trades even at 4-5 around his W stun zone placement."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your clone Pop Blossom out-engages him; his R Chronobreak is only defensive."},{"when":"1st item","text":"W-stun combo plus Chronobreak heal-back wins his extended trades and all-ins."},{"when":"Late","text":"His mobility dodges your burst and R erases it — group and bait his W instead of dueling."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade when he Qs for CS before he has Phase Dive","Root him at level 3 out of his escape","Bait his W-E combo with your clone in fights"],"foe":["Poke with Q Timewinder and place W for stun setups","All-in with the W-stun combo once items are online","Roam and pick with E-W-Q, healing back via Chronobreak"]},"early":"Ekko is weak and mana-hungry in the first levels; he pokes with Q Timewinder but the return hit is easy to dodge, and he has no escape until E Phase Dive at 3. Walk up whenever he Qs for CS and trade with autos into Q Blooming Burst — he can't sustain those exchanges early. Deny his W Parallel Convergence value by not standing still inside its zone. Levels 1-2 are yours.","mid":"Level 3 stays in your favour — E Tangle-Barbs roots him before he can E Phase Dive out, giving a clean Q burst. Levels 4-5 even out as his W stun zone and Q slow let him trade and set up ganks; play around whether his W is placed near you. Level 6 swings back to you: your Pop Blossom out-of-clone engage beats his, and his R Chronobreak is defensive, so if you all-in and he R's away you still won the tempo. Track his roams — Ekko loves to E-W-Q a side lane, so ping and match him.","late":"With items Ekko's combo becomes lethal: W stun into Q-E-auto plus R Chronobreak to heal back any damage you deal means he wins extended trades and all-ins. His mobility lets him dodge your Q and R, and Chronobreak simply erases your burst. Don't duel him past first item — instead group, and use your clone so he blows W-E onto the wrong target. Ward for his roams because his pick potential in the mid-game is his real strength.","whys":["Ekko is mana-starved with no escape, so your step-up trades win.","He still can't punish your autos into Q without a dash.","Your E-root lands before Phase Dive exists, giving a clean burst.","His W stun zone and Q slow even the trades around positioning.","Your clone Pop Blossom out-engages his defensive-only Chronobreak.","W-stun combo plus Chronobreak heal-back wins his extended fights.","His mobility and R healing erase your burst in any straight duel."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"fizz","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Bait his E Playful/Trickster untargetable with your clone, then punish the recovery frames with Q."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pre-stun his R Chum the Waters all-in with Pop Blossom as his E dodge window expires."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You still out-trade him 1v1; his real danger is roaming, so match his tempo."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fizz picks map-wide — ward and follow; your R turns his in-lane all-in on reaction."}],"wants":{"you":["Auto-poke him every time he walks up to CS","Bait his E untargetable with your clone, then punish","Pre-stun his R all-in with Pop Blossom"],"foe":["Use Q Urchin Strike to trade and dodge out with E","All-in with R Chum the Waters plus ignite once he has items","Roam and pick side lanes rather than duel you"]},"early":"Fizz is melee and has to walk into auto range to farm, so you own the early levels — poke him with autos into Q Blooming Burst every time he steps to last-hit, and he has no answer until his E is up. His Q Urchin Strike is a gap-closer he'll use to CS, but that puts him inside your return-trade range. Keep the wave slightly on your side so he takes minion aggro and tower pressure when he dives for a cannon. Levels 1-2 are firmly yours.","mid":"You stay ahead through the mid levels because your combo out-trades his and your kit answers his engage. When he Q-E's onto you, drop Q Blooming Burst where he'll land and use W Shapesplitter clone to bait his E Playful/Trickster untargetable window, then punish the instant it ends. At 6 your Pop Blossom stun catches him the moment his E dodge expires or as he R Chum the Waters onto you — you can pre-stun the whole all-in. Manage mana and don't over-extend, since a shark throw plus ignite is his one kill combo.","late":"Even with items you hold the lane edge: Fizz is an assassin who wants to roam and pick, so his threat is map-wide rather than a straight duel he loses. In lane, your R Pop Blossom and clone let you survive or turn his all-in — bait the E untargetable, then stun. His R Chum the Waters is his engage and your R can beat it on reaction. Track his roams and match them, because his even win rate comes from picks elsewhere, not from beating you one-on-one.","whys":["Melee Fizz must walk into your auto range to farm, so you out-poke him.","He has no answer to your step-up trades before his E is online.","Your combo out-trades his and your clone baits his E dodge.","You punish the recovery frames after his Playful/Trickster window.","Pop Blossom pre-stuns his R all-in as his untargetability ends.","You still win the 1v1; his even win rate comes from roams, not lane.","Your R turns his all-in on reaction, so the lane stays yours."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"galio","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"E-root into layered Q petals beats his W damage reduction and his short E Justice Punch range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R Hero's Entrance is a roam tool, not a duel — shove and match him when he channels to leave."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Galio can't out-damage you 1v1; his value is map-wide, so deny his roams."},{"when":"Late","text":"He scales as a utility tank — track his R ganks and out-farm him in lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Q Winds of War and trade after his W shield is spent","Root with E and layer Q petals through his damage reduction","Shove and match his R Hero's Entrance roams"],"foe":["Poke with Q Winds of War and soak trades with W Shield of Durand","Save R Hero's Entrance to gank another lane","Scale into a teamfight taunt-and-roam utility role"]},"early":"You out-damage Galio in a straight lane from level 1 — his Q Winds of War is his only poke and it's slow and easy to sidestep, while his empowered auto is on a cooldown you can dodge. Walk up and trade with autos into Q Blooming Burst; he'll rely on W Shield of Durand to soak it, so trade after the shield is spent or bait it out first. Levels 1-2 are yours as long as you don't stand in the center of his Q.","mid":"You keep the advantage through the mid levels. E Tangle-Barbs roots him for a Q burst, and his short-range E Justice Punch is his only engage — respect it, but you out-range and out-burst him. His W damage reduction blunts single hits, so layer your Q petals to force multiple instances of damage instead of one. At 6 his R Hero's Entrance is usually saved to roam-assist another lane rather than duel you; when he channels R to leave, shove the wave and either match the roam or take a free plate. Deny his roam value.","late":"The lane stays yours because Galio scales as a roaming utility tank, not a mid-lane duelist — he won't out-damage you 1v1 even with items. His threat is R Hero's Entrance ganks and teamfight W taunts, so the game is about tracking his roams, not the lane duel. Keep the wave pushing so he can't leave without losing farm, and use your own clone-roams to match his map pressure. Straight up, your burst beats his kit through every item stage.","whys":["You out-damage Galio's slow single-Q poke from level 1.","Your auto-into-Q trades beat his shield-reliant exchanges.","E-root plus layered Q petals punch through his W damage reduction.","You out-range and out-burst his short E Justice Punch engage.","His R is a roam tool, not a duel answer, so lane control stays yours.","Galio can't out-damage you 1v1; deny his map-wide value instead.","As a utility tank he never out-duels your burst through the item stages."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"hwei","win":["Hwei","Hwei","Neeko","Hwei","Skill","Skill","Hwei"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 is your one clean window: with Q, W, and E you can W-clone bait a QW disengage read, then land Tangle-Barbs on the doubled hitbox and follow with Blooming Burst before Hwei repositions with his E dashaway lantern."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom unlocks but Hwei's kit is built to zone your channel; save R for when his EW (Stirring Lachesis) fear or Grim Visage is on cooldown, otherwise you leap into a full disciplinary combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On Luden's/Liandry's your all-in burst spikes, but so does Hwei's poke ceiling from QE (Devastating Fissure); trade windows stay roughly even, so pick off sidelanes with roams instead of forcing lane."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Hwei out-ranges and out-zones you in every extended fight; convert your R engage into picks on his carries in the fog rather than dueling him head-on through his full QQ-QE-QW spellbook."}],"wants":{"you":["Fog and flanks so your R lands before he sees the clone","A clouddrake/sidelane roam to escape his lane zoning","Jungle ganks while his E disengage is down"],"foe":["Long open lanes to free-cast QW poke and QE zoning","You stepping onto minions inside QE cast range","Vision so he pre-fires abilities on your R channel"]},"early":"Hwei wins the early cast war outright: his QW (Severing Bolt) and QE punish any minion you walk up to, and at level 1-2 you have no clone leverage yet, so you simply lose the ranged poke exchange. Hold the melee-adjacent caster line, soak XP, and don't int a level-1 cheese.","mid":"Level 3 gives you your only real spike as your full Q-W-E combo out-bursts his single ability, but from level 4 onward his layered QE zoning and EW fear reassert control of the lane. Use Shapesplitter clones to fake commits and roam on wave-push timers rather than trading raw poke.","late":"Once Hwei completes his first item his spellbook out-ranges and out-zones you at every stage, so a straight duel loses. Play through vision and your ultimate as a flank engage tool onto his backline, catching squishies before he can respond with his disengage E.","whys":["Level 1 Hwei's QW and QE poke punish your melee-range caster pattern before any clone leverage exists.","Level 2 he still out-pokes you two-for-one with his ranged spellbook while you lack a full combo.","Level 3 your complete Q-W-E burst finally out-damages his single available ability, giving you the trade.","Levels 4-5 his stacked QE zoning and cooldowns reassert lane control over your short windows.","Level 6 is even because your R threat and his EW fear/disengage cancel each other out.","At first item both spike into burst-versus-poke parity, so neither clearly wins the trade.","Two-plus items in, Hwei's superior range and zoning out-scale your all-in in extended fights."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"irelia","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Q, W, and E online you dominate the level 3-5 window: throw Tangle-Barbs to root when she Q-dashes onto a minion, then drop Blooming Burst on the marked target so her Bladesurge resets can't outrun your rooted burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom is a hard answer to her all-in; if she E (Flawless Duet) stuns you, R still detonates from stealth or clone, and you can W-clone bait her ult wall then leap her for the kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Luden's/Liandry's spike lets you one-combo her before four Q resets ramp her damage; she has no sustain in her kit, so a single rooted Q-E-R rotation deletes her health bar."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you still hold the pick pattern: catch her with E from fog before she can Q onto a minion, since without a dash target she is a low-range melee with no escape."}],"wants":{"you":["Short waves so she can't Q-reset through your minions safely","E rooting her the instant she dashes in with Bladesurge","A slow-push to set up 6 roams while she's stuck farming"],"foe":["A big minion wave to chain Q resets and stick to you","You wasting E on a clone/whiff so her all-in is free","Side-lane isolation to snowball with Trinity Force resets"]},"early":"You control levels 1-2 comfortably: Irelia is a weak, mana-starved laner before her passive stacks, and your poke plus clone pressure means she can't Q-reset onto you without eating Tangle-Barbs. Keep the wave central and deny her free stacks off caster minions.","mid":"From level 3 through 6 this is squarely your lane. Your instant Q-E burst punishes every Bladesurge engage, E is a point-blank root that stops her mid-dash, and Pop Blossom answers her Flawless Duet all-in cleanly. Manage the wave short so she never gets a safe reset chain, and roam on push timings.","late":"Even two-plus items deep you keep the initiative through picks. Irelia needs a dash target to function, so E-rooting her from a flank or fog leaves her stranded; land the root, combo, and she folds before her resets ramp because her kit carries no sustain or hard escape.","whys":["Level 1 Irelia is mana-hungry and weak, so your clone pressure and poke control the lane.","Level 2 she still can't reset safely into your Tangle-Barbs, keeping you ahead.","Level 3 your full Q-E-W burst punishes every Bladesurge dash, dominating trades.","Levels 4-5 you out-trade her resets because E roots her mid-dash before she sticks.","Level 6 Pop Blossom hard-answers her Flawless Duet all-in, so the window is yours.","At first item your combo deletes her before four Q resets ramp, and she has no sustain.","Two-plus items in you still pick her off with E from fog since she needs a dash target."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"karma","win":["Karma","Karma","Karma","Karma","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Karma's zone: her RQ-empowered Inner Flame (Mantra) roots and out-ranges everything you have, so avoid the poke war and use W-clone to fake commits while you soak XP under tower."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom flips the lane: Karma has no hard escape beyond her E shield-speed, so bait her Mantra-Q, then leap in with R from a clone for a burst she can't shield through."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Luden's/Liandry's spike lets a rooted Q-E-R combo kill her before her Mantra cooldown returns; she only has one empowered cast, so once RQ is down she's a squishy with no burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you out-teamfight her: your R AoE and clone flanks punish her low range, and she can only shield-speed one ally while your burst deletes her from fog before she reacts."}],"wants":{"you":["Waves crashing so you reach 6 and flip the lane","E rooting her the moment her Mantra shield-speed is down","Fog flanks to leap R before she can RE peel"],"foe":["Long lanes to chunk you with Mantra-Q roots from max range","You walking up while her RQ is charged","Early skirmishes before your R comes online"]},"early":"Karma owns levels 1-4 outright: her Mantra empowers Inner Flame into a long-range rooting nuke from level 3, and she out-pokes and out-ranges your entire pre-6 kit. Don't contest the caster line for CS you can't safely take; hold under tower, dodge her Q, and give up minor plates rather than eat RQ chunks.","mid":"The lane inverts the instant you hit 6. Pop Blossom gives you an all-in Karma can't outrun once her Mantra-Q or RE peel is spent, so track her Mantra cooldown and commit through a W-clone when it's down. Your rooted Q-E-R burst kills her before the empowered cast returns.","late":"Post-first-item you keep the upper hand in every skirmish and teamfight. Karma is a low-range enchanter-mage hybrid with only shield-speed to save herself, so E-rooting her from a flank leads straight into a lethal combo, and your R AoE swings grouped fights before she can peel a single carry.","whys":["Level 1 Karma out-ranges you and threatens early Q poke you can't answer.","Level 2 her superior range keeps chunking you before your combo exists.","Level 3 her Mantra-empowered rooting Inner Flame dominates the poke war.","Levels 4-5 she still controls the lane with long-range RQ roots and shields.","Level 6 Pop Blossom flips it: she has no escape from your all-in once Mantra is spent.","At first item your rooted combo kills her before her single empowered cast returns.","Two-plus items in your R AoE and flanks out-teamfight her low-range peel."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"kassadin","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Punish Kassadin hard while he's a helpless melee: land Tangle-Barbs on the wave, drop Blooming Burst, and every time he walks up to last-hit you get a free Q-E chunk he can't answer pre-6."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Riftwalk arrives but yours is scarier early; if he R's onto you, Pop Blossom from stealth or clone punishes the low-mana blink, and you can W-clone bait the escape then leap for the kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Race his item timing: on Luden's/Liandry's your rooted Q-E-R still one-combos him before Rod of Ages and Rylai's give him the HP and mana to spam Riftwalk safely."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items is his scaling zone, so end the game on your lead: use R flanks to catch him before he stacks Riftwalk, and coordinate jungle dives on short waves to deny his farm."}],"wants":{"you":["Fast pushes to shove him under tower and deny early farm","Roams and dives while he's a weak pre-6 melee","E rooting him before he can Riftwalk away"],"foe":["A passive lane to scale untouched to his item spikes","Rod of Ages and Rylai's stacking so Riftwalk spam is safe","The game dragging past three items into his hyperscale"]},"early":"You crush levels 1-2: Kassadin is one of the weakest early melees in the game, forced to walk into caster range where your poke and clone pressure punish every last-hit. Shove the wave, chunk him off CS, and set up the tempo to roam or invite a gank while he's defenseless.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay firmly yours. His only trade tool is a spellshield and short-range poke, so your instant Q-E burst wins every exchange, and even when Riftwalk unlocks your R punishes the low-mana blink. Keep the wave shoving so he bleeds farm and you dictate roam timers.","late":"Kassadin is the definition of a scaling threat, so your entire job late is to close before he does. Post-first-item your combo still deletes him pre-Rod-of-Ages; use R as a flank engage to catch him off-guard and coordinate dives on pushed waves so he never reaches the three-item window where Riftwalk becomes untouchable.","whys":["Level 1 Kassadin is a helpless melee forced into your poke range.","Level 2 you keep chunking him off every last-hit with impunity.","Level 3 your full Q-E burst outclasses his short-range pre-6 tools.","Levels 4-5 he still can't trade back, so you dominate and deny farm.","Level 6 your R punishes his low-mana Riftwalk before he can scale.","At first item your rooted combo one-shots him before Rod of Ages saves him.","Two-plus items in you still out-tempo him by closing before his hyperscale lands."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"katarina","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Katarina","Katarina","Katarina"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Levels 3-5 are your window: Tangle-Barbs roots her the instant she E-blinks to a dagger, cancelling her reset pattern, so land the root and Blooming Burst before she can pick up the blade and dash out."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both ults arrive but hers snowballs harder; if you commit R, she can Shunpo away or Death Lotus through it, so hold Pop Blossom as a peel/reactive tool rather than an engage she can reset off."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Katarina's item spike lets her chain E resets after a pick, and her Death Lotus out-DPSes your single combo; play safe, ward daggers, and don't give her a kill to snowball resets in a fight."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in she is a reset monster in teamfights while you have one burst rotation; group tight, save E to interrupt her Death Lotus, and never let her flank a low target to start the reset chain."}],"wants":{"you":["E rooting her mid-blink to cancel her dagger resets","Short waves so she can't safely dash to daggers","Grouped play where your E interrupts her Death Lotus"],"foe":["A stray kill to start snowballing E resets","Daggers scattered on a big wave for free Shunpo dashes","Isolated picks so Death Lotus channels uninterrupted"]},"early":"You hold levels 1-3: before her resets come online Katarina is a squishy melee, and your poke plus a well-timed Tangle-Barbs root punish every time she steps up to a dagger. Deny her early kills at all costs, because her entire threat scales off snowballing resets you can starve now.","mid":"Level 4-5 is skill-dependent as her dagger-reset pattern comes online and duels come down to whether you land E to cancel her blink. From level 6 the lane tilts toward Katarina: her ultimate out-DPSes your single combo and gives her reset fuel, so stop dueling and play for her to overextend into your jungler.","late":"Post-first-item Katarina is one of the scariest reset threats in a teamfight while you carry only one burst rotation. Your job is discipline: ward daggers, hold Tangle-Barbs to interrupt her Death Lotus channel, and stay grouped so she can never flank an isolated squishy to ignite the E-reset chain that ends fights.","whys":["Level 1 Katarina is a resetless squishy melee your poke controls.","Level 2 you keep punishing her step-ups before her pattern exists.","Level 3 your root and burst cancel her early dagger dashes.","Levels 4-5 the trade is skill-based on whether you land E to stop her blink.","Level 6 her Death Lotus out-DPSes your combo and fuels resets.","At first item her reset chains and ult DPS outpace your single rotation.","Two-plus items in she's a teamfight reset monster you can only try to interrupt."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"leblanc","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","LeBlanc","LeBlanc","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Levels 3-5 are yours: when she Q-W engages, throw Tangle-Barbs to root her before the W returns, then Blooming Burst punishes the fact she's used her only escape to get onto you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R gives a second W-style reposition, so her burst-and-blink combo out-trades your single rotation; hold Pop Blossom as an anti-assassin reactive and don't face-check her chain when W is up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On her first item LeBlanc's Q-R-W combo one-shots squishies and she can flank your sidelanes freely; respect her roam timers, ward, and don't push up without knowing her W is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two-plus items you reclaim the edge: her assassin burst falls off into your AoE teamfight R and clone flanks, and if she W's in and whiffs the kill your Q-E-R deletes her before the double blink resets."}],"wants":{"you":["E rooting her mid Q-W so she can't blink back out","Grouped late fights where your R AoE beats her single-target burst","Warded flanks to punish a whiffed W engage"],"foe":["The 6-to-two-item window to R-Q-W one-shot a squishy","You pushed up blind so she can W-flank for a pick","Sidelane isolation to snowball her roam kills"]},"early":"You control levels 1-4: LeBlanc's engage is Q into W, and the moment she blinks onto you Tangle-Barbs roots her before the W recast is available to escape, turning her all-in into a free trade for you. Hold the wave central, punish her committed W, and deny the early kill her whole game snowballs from.","mid":"Levels 5-6 tilt to LeBlanc as her ultimate hands her a second reposition and her Q-R-W burst out-trades your single combo, letting her flank and one-shot on roams. Stop face-checking, track her W cooldown, and play the map safe until this power spike passes and your teamfight scaling takes over.","late":"By two-plus items the lane swings back to you. LeBlanc's single-target assassin burst falls off relative to your AoE R and clone-flank teamfighting, and any time she W's in and fails to instantly kill, your rooted Q-E-R punishes her before the double blink comes back up. Group, hold vision, and make her commitments lethal.","whys":["Level 1 you soak safely while her single-target kit can't burst you yet.","Level 2 your poke and clone pressure keep her committed engages risky.","Level 3 your root punishes her Q-W the instant she blinks in.","Levels 4-5 you still out-trade her before her ult reposition exists.","Level 6 her R gives a second blink and her Q-R-W out-bursts your combo.","At first item her assassin burst one-shots squishies and roams freely.","Two-plus items in her single-target damage falls off to your AoE teamfight."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"lissandra","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Lissandra","Lissandra","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early you can punish her mana-hungry clear, but from level 4 her Q claw poke and E (Glacial Path) safety let her farm through your pressure; don't overstay against her PQ poke wall."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Frozen Tomb is a point-blank self-peel that hard-answers your Pop Blossom leap, so if she R's herself when you jump, your channel gets zoned; hold R and bait her Tomb before committing."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you finish Luden's/Liandry's your rooted Q-E burst out-damages her utility kit, and she has to use E to escape rather than trade, so pick her off when Glacial Path is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you out-teamfight her: she's a lockdown utility mage with low solo kill pressure, so your R AoE and clone flanks let you delete her carries before her single R-and-Tomb combo matters."}],"wants":{"you":["First item online so your combo out-damages her utility","E rooting her when Glacial Path is on cooldown","Grouped fights where R AoE beats her single lockdown"],"foe":["The 4-6 window to poke with Q claws and farm safely","You leaping in so she Frozen Tombs to zone your channel","A slow scaling game leaning on her CC utility"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 lean your way as Lissandra is mana-constrained and can't fully answer your poke and clone pressure while she manages her clear. Chunk her when she steps up for CS, but bank the wave and tempo now, because her lane control is about to tighten from level 4.","mid":"Levels 4-5 tilt to Lissandra: her Q claw poke and Glacial Path E give her a safe, spammable zoning pattern that out-farms your short trade windows, and at 6 Frozen Tomb is a self-cast peel that shuts down your Pop Blossom all-in. Bait her Tomb and E before you ever commit R.","late":"From your first item onward the matchup swings back to you. Your rooted Q-E-R burst out-damages her utility-focused kit, so catch her whenever Glacial Path is on cooldown, and in grouped fights your AoE R and clone flanks out-teamfight a mage whose value is single-target lockdown rather than raw kill pressure.","whys":["Level 1 Lissandra is mana-hungry and can't answer your early poke.","Level 2 your clone pressure keeps her honest while she manages clear.","Level 3 your full combo still out-trades her before her poke ramps.","Levels 4-5 her Q claws and Glacial Path zone and out-farm your windows.","Level 6 Frozen Tomb self-peels and shuts down your Pop Blossom leap.","At first item your rooted burst out-damages her utility kit and catches her.","Two-plus items in your AoE R out-teamfights her single-target lockdown."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"locke","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With all three abilities online your combo is Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst on the slowed target; land the E and the matchup swings, whiff it and you are simply shoving. Nothing here is auto-won, so treat every all-in as a coin-flip you tilt with clean skillshots."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is the one window that leans against you: Locke's level-6 power lets him answer your Pop Blossom engage and punish the channel. Do not walk in for R first unless he has burned his ultimate, or you get bursted mid-cast."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first mythic (Liandry's/Lich Bane line) your Q clears waves in one rotation and your all-in threat returns to even footing. Look to convert prio into scuttle and river skirmishes rather than a solo kill you are not favoured for."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights your R off a Shapesplitter-clone flank is your whole payoff; both of you are equal threats, so let him commit first and punish the follow-up window."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E (Tangle-Barbs) before committing Q","Use W clone to bait his level-6 answer","Play for even trades, not solo kills"],"foe":["Hit his level-6 spike before you find yours","Punish your Pop Blossom channel on engage","Trade back whenever you step up to cast Q"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are dead even: both of you are farming, kill pressure is minimal, and whoever lands their point-blank ability first wins a small trade. Hold Tangle-Barbs and last-hit safely; there is no lane-dominant side here, so do not overstep for a first blood that isn't there.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay a skill check. Your Q-E combo out-damages his poke if you land the root, but a whiffed E leaves you shoved and vulnerable, and at 6 his ultimate window is the single phase that tips his way. Ping your jungler for any all-in past 6 rather than soloing it.","late":"Into items the lane normalises to even. Your teamfight R and clone flank are strong, but so is his kit; farm your mythic, group, and win through picks and objective setups rather than expecting to run him down 1v1.","whys":["Level 1 is even because both champions are farming point-blank with no reliable kill setup.","Level 2 is a skill trade — whoever lands their second ability first wins a marginal exchange.","Level 3 hinges on you landing Tangle-Barbs, so the phase reads as an even skill check.","Levels 4-5 stay even as both of you trade roam and shove windows without a hard advantage.","Level 6 tips to Locke because his ultimate spike answers and punishes your Pop Blossom engage.","At first item the lane resets to even as your Q clear and all-in threat come back online.","With two-plus items both of you are equal teamfight threats, so the phase stays a skill matchup."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"lux","win":["Lux","Lux","Neeko","Lux","Skill","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"At 3 you finally out-trade her: Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst on a Lux who just used Light Binding is a huge chunk she cannot answer while Q is down. But at 4-5 her Lucent Singularity (E) plus Light Binding poke chips you every time you step to CS, so pick your all-in the moment her Q is on cooldown and otherwise respect the range gap."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even window. Final Spark can execute you out of a trade, but your Pop Blossom off a Shapesplitter clone flank threatens the same one-shot on her. Whoever lands their setup first wins, so don't R into a full-health, Q-up Lux."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your spike arrives here: with your mythic online, a single E-Q-R rotation from a clone angle deletes a squishy Lux who has no mobility. This is where the 55% win rate lives — punish every missed Light Binding hard."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights you are the bigger threat: clone flank, land Tangle-Barbs on the carry, and Pop Blossom deletes Lux before she casts. She only wins if she catches you with a blind Q first."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in the instant her Light Binding (Q) is down","Use W clone to flank past her poke range","Farm to first item, then punish her immobility"],"foe":["Poke you with E+Q from max range pre-6","Land Light Binding to zone your CS","Keep Q up so you can never step in safely"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Lux. Light Binding and Lucent Singularity out-range your entire kit, so she pokes you for free while you try to last-hit, and stepping up only feeds her another Q. Soak XP, dodge her skillshots, and accept you will lose a little HP before your combo comes online.","mid":"At 3 the lane flips to you the moment her Q is on cooldown — Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst out-damages anything she can return. But levels 4-5 swing back to Lux as her E+Q poke and wave zoning punish you between all-in windows. Play the Q-timer: aggressive when Light Binding is down, passive when it is up. At 6 it is an even race between the two ultimates.","late":"Once you finish your mythic the matchup is firmly yours, which is why the win rate sits above even. Lux is immobile and squishy; a clone-flank E-Q-R one-shots her, and in teamfights you are the far bigger threat as long as you don't eat a blind Light Binding.","whys":["Level 1 favours Lux because Light Binding and her auto range let her poke you with no answer.","Level 2 stays Lux's as her second ability extends the poke and zone control you cannot match.","Level 3 flips to Neeko since your E-Q combo out-trades her the moment Light Binding is spent.","Levels 4-5 return to Lux as her E+Q poke chips you between your all-in windows.","Level 6 is even — both ultimates threaten a kill, decided by who lands their setup first.","At first item Neeko spikes: your burst one-shots an immobile Lux who missed her Q.","With two-plus items Neeko dominates teamfights, deleting a squishy Lux from a clone flank."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"malzahar","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Skill","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is your entire kill window. Malzahar has no mobility, no burst, and nothing to punish aggression before 6, so walk up and land Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst repeatedly. Push the wave in and force him to sit in the DoT range of your Q; if you can crash a wave and all-in before his voidlings stack, you take the lane over."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even, and dangerous. Nether Grasp suppresses you point-blank and his Q silence stops your combo, so a face-check into a full-HP Malz can get you killed. Only all-in past 6 when his R is down or you have QSS/summoners up — otherwise keep poking from your Q range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even. His Malefic Visions waveclear and self-peel ult trade off against your burst and roam threat. Use your superior early lead to roam and set up your jungler rather than forcing a fight into his suppress."},{"when":"Late","text":"The matchup slips to Malzahar here: with Zhonya's, Rylai's and a maxed ult he farms safely and R-locks you or your carry out of every teamfight. Build QSS/Mercurial, don't get caught, and try to end before his scaling and lockdown outweigh your early lead."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in hard levels 3-5 before he has any answer","Shove the wave and deny him free farm","Convert your early lead into roams before he scales"],"foe":["Survive to 6 and outscale with safe waveclear","Land Nether Grasp suppress or Q silence to flip a trade","Reach 2+ items where his lockdown and DoT take over"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours outright. Malzahar is one of the weakest early laners in the game with no mobility and no trade tools, so you can walk up, land Tangle-Barbs, and poke him off the wave with impunity. Set up a slow push and make his last-hitting miserable.","mid":"Levels 3-5 are your kill window — your full E-Q all-in out-damages anything he can do, and he cannot escape it. But at 6 the phase evens out: Nether Grasp suppresses you and his Q silences your combo, so a careless dive into his ult trades your lead away. Be aggressive before 6, respectful after, and only commit when his R is on cooldown.","late":"Malzahar is a scaling menace, and by two-plus items the matchup turns against you. Zhonya's plus his point-and-click suppress means he farms safely and removes you from fights on demand. Your job is to snowball the early lead into towers and objectives before his lockdown and DoT damage take over the late game.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko because Malzahar has no early trade tools to answer your walk-up.","Level 2 stays Neeko's as he still cannot punish your poke or aggression.","Level 3 is Neeko's kill window — your E-Q all-in beats his immobile passive laning.","Levels 4-5 remain Neeko's as you dictate the wave before his voidlings and ult come online.","Level 6 evens out because Nether Grasp and his Q silence can flip any careless all-in.","At first item it stays even — his waveclear and self-peel offset your burst and roam threat.","With two-plus items Malzahar takes over, scaling with safe farm and point-click suppress lockdown."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"mel","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Mel"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You own this window. Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst out-trades her early, but you must respect Rebuttal (W) — cast your abilities when her reflect is down, never into it, or you eat your own root and burst. Punish the moments she has W on cooldown and you win every exchange."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still yours. Pop Blossom off a Shapesplitter clone flank one-shots a squishy Mel before her scaling matters, and she has no reliable escape. Look for the R kill or a roam here while your tempo lead is real."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You are still ahead on your first mythic — your burst combo kills her outright and your roam threat is higher. This is the last phase where you hold the advantage, so cash it in for kills, plates and objectives before she comes online."},{"when":"Late","text":"The matchup flips hard: by two-plus items Mel out-ranges you, reflects your engage with Rebuttal, and her ultimate dominates teamfights. The sub-50% win rate lives here — you must end the game before her scaling erases your early lead."}],"wants":{"you":["Cast Q and E only when Rebuttal (W) is down","All-in and snowball hard before two items","Close the game out before her scaling takes over"],"foe":["Reflect your combo with Rebuttal to punish engages","Survive lane and reach her item spikes","Out-range and out-scale you in extended teamfights"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: your point-blank trades out-damage Mel's early poke and she has no way to punish your walk-up. The single rule is Rebuttal — if you throw Tangle-Barbs or Blooming Burst into her W reflect, you take your own damage and root, so bait or wait it out before committing.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay in your favour. Your full combo out-trades her, and at 6 a clone-flank Pop Blossom simply deletes a squishy, immobile Mel. Play aggressive around her W cooldown, shove and roam, and build the biggest lead you can — because this advantage has an expiry date.","late":"This is a scaling matchup that turns on you, and the below-even win rate reflects it. Once Mel hits two-plus items she out-ranges your combo, reflects your all-in with Rebuttal, and her ultimate takes over fights. Convert every ounce of your early lead into towers and objectives and try to end before she scales past you.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko because your point-blank trades out-damage Mel's early poke.","Level 2 stays Neeko's as she has no tool to punish your walk-up aggression.","Level 3 is Neeko's — your E-Q all-in out-trades her whenever Rebuttal is down.","Levels 4-5 remain Neeko's as you dictate the wave and threaten the all-in.","Level 6 is Neeko's because a clone-flank Pop Blossom one-shots a squishy, immobile Mel.","At first item Neeko still leads on burst and roam threat before her scaling arrives.","With two-plus items Mel takes over, out-ranging, reflecting, and out-scaling you in fights."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"naafiri","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Naafiri","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You control this range war. Naafiri wants to shove and poke with Darkin Daggers (Q), but your Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst out-trades her whenever she steps up to recall her daggers. Dodge The Pack (W) — it's her only gap-closer and her all-in engine — and she is left poking harmlessly while you set the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still yours if you play it right. Her R gives move speed and packmates, but a clone-flank Pop Blossom out-bursts a lethality Naafiri who has no defensive layer. Hold Tangle-Barbs for her W dash-in and you win the 6 all-in; just don't get caught flat-footed by W-E."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is her spike and the one phase to fear: her first lethality item plus packmates lets her W-in, E, and delete you in one rotation. Buy an early Seeker's/Zhonya's component, hug your wave, and do not sidestep into a bush where she can dagger-reset and all-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"The game swings back to you. As a single-target assassin Naafiri falls off into your AoE — clone-flank Pop Blossom and Blooming Burst hit her whole team, and Zhonya's blanks her all-in. Play for teamfights, not sidelane duels, and you outscale her cleanly."}],"wants":{"you":["Win ranged trades when her daggers are mid-flight","Dodge The Pack (W) to strand her all-in","Buy early armor and scale into AoE teamfights"],"foe":["Shove and poke with Darkin Daggers","Hit her first lethality spike to burst you in one W-E rotation","Catch you isolated before you build armor"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: you out-range Naafiri's early poke and can punish her every time she walks up to collect her daggers. She has no all-in yet, so trade with Tangle-Barbs freely and set up a slow push to deny her tempo.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay in your favour as long as you respect The Pack. Your combo out-damages her poke, and even at 6 a clone-flank Pop Blossom out-bursts a squishy lethality assassin. Dodging her W dash is the whole game here — land your root on it and her only engage tool is wasted.","late":"The danger phase is her first lethality item, where W-E plus packmates can one-shot you — so itemize armor early and play safe through it. Past that, the matchup is yours again: Naafiri is single-target and falls off into your AoE, Zhonya's blanks her burst, and your teamfight clone combo hits her entire team. Group and scale.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko because you out-range Naafiri's early dagger poke.","Level 2 stays Neeko's as she has no all-in and you punish her walk-ups.","Level 3 is Neeko's — your E-Q combo out-trades her whenever her daggers are mid-flight.","Levels 4-5 remain Neeko's as you set the wave and dodge her only gap-closer.","Level 6 stays Neeko's since a clone-flank Pop Blossom out-bursts a squishy lethality Naafiri.","At first item Naafiri spikes: her lethality plus packmates delete you in one W-E rotation.","With two-plus items Neeko recovers as a single-target assassin falls off into your AoE and Zhonya's."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"orianna","win":["Orianna","Orianna","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Skill","Orianna"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is your window and it hinges on ball position. When Orianna's ball is out on the wave or shielding a minion, she is defenceless — Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst all-ins the ball-less Ori and she cannot peel herself. Watch where the ball sits; step in the instant it is away from her, and back off when she is holding it for the Q-E poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even. Command Shockwave can catch you and set up her jungler, but your Pop Blossom off a clone flank threatens the same game-ending combo. It becomes a setup war — don't R into a braced Ori with her ball on herself, and bait her Shockwave before you commit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even. Her waveclear and Q-E poke offset your burst and roam threat, so neither of you snowballs the lane hard. Use your mid-game all-in edge to roam and skirmish rather than forcing a fight into her ball."},{"when":"Late","text":"Orianna takes over the late game: her Shockwave is one of the best teamfight ultimates in the class, and her shields plus range let her control fights from safety. Your job is to catch her before the fight starts — clone flank, land the root — because in a clean 5v5 her ball dictates the tempo."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in the moment her ball is away from her body","Punish poke windows only when Command Attack is down","Roam with your mid-game tempo edge"],"foe":["Poke you with Command Attack + ball zoning pre-3","Keep her ball on herself to deny your all-in","Reach teamfights where Command Shockwave dominates"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Orianna. Her ball lets her Command Attack and zone you off the wave from range, chipping you every time you step to CS while you have no way to trade back. Soak XP, respect the ball's threat range, and wait for your combo to come online.","mid":"Levels 3-5 flip to you and it is all about the ball. Whenever Orianna sends it out to poke or clear, she has no self-peel, and your E-Q all-in punishes her instantly. Track the ball, commit when it is off her body, and hold back when she is bracing with it on herself. At 6 the lane evens into a Shockwave-versus-Pop Blossom setup war.","late":"This is a scaling matchup that tilts back to Orianna, even though your mid-game kill pressure keeps the overall win rate on your side. Her Command Shockwave and shields make her a premier teamfighter, so avoid clean 5v5s into her ball — instead use your clone flank to catch her out and burst her before she can turn the fight.","whys":["Level 1 favours Orianna because her ball lets her Command Attack and zone you from range.","Level 2 stays Orianna's as her W extends the ball control and poke you cannot answer.","Level 3 flips to Neeko — you all-in the ball-less Ori the moment her ball is on the wave.","Levels 4-5 stay Neeko's as you punish every out-of-position ball with your E-Q combo.","Level 6 is even: Command Shockwave and Pop Blossom threaten each other in a setup war.","At first item it stays even — her poke and waveclear offset your burst and roam threat.","With two-plus items Orianna takes over, controlling teamfights with Shockwave and shields."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"pantheon","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-range and out-scale him from the first back. Pantheon wants to Comet Spear (Q) poke and then W-Q all-in, but Tangle-Barbs into Blooming Burst out-damages his kit if you dodge the Shield Vault stun. Keep the wave near your side, hold E for his W leap, and every time he commits without it he loses the trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still yours in lane, but his Grand Starfall is a global roam threat — the danger is a side lane, not you. Ping the R the moment he backs out, and in a 1v1 your clone-flank Pop Blossom out-bursts a squishy Pantheon who can only Aegis-block one direction."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your spike, his fall-off. Once your mythic is online your burst overwhelms an AD bruiser with no ranged scaling, while his damage plateaus. Punish his shorter range hard, deny his roams, and snowball the tempo lead."},{"when":"Late","text":"Firmly yours. Pantheon is a single-target melee who blocks damage from only one angle with Aegis Assault; a clone flank plus Pop Blossom deletes him and hits his whole team. He is a diminished threat in a 5v5 while you are a primary one."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Shield Vault (W) and punish his committed all-ins","Out-range his Comet Spear poke","Flank with your clone past his Aegis block"],"foe":["Land W stun into Q for an early all-in","Snowball a side lane with Grand Starfall roams","Force short melee trades before your combo is up"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: you out-range Comet Spear and can trade back on any Pantheon who steps up without his W. His whole game is landing Shield Vault to start an all-in, so sidestep it, hold your root for his leap, and he is left poking with a short-range spear while you control the wave.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay in your favour. Your E-Q combo out-damages his all-in as long as you respect the W stun, and even at 6 a clone-flank Pop Blossom out-bursts him one-on-one. His ultimate is a global roam tool, not a lane-kill, so the real threat is your side lanes — ping every Grand Starfall and track his recalls.","late":"The matchup is comfortably yours into items. Pantheon is a single-target melee bruiser who plateaus while your burst scales, and Aegis Assault only blocks one direction — a clone flank simply goes around it. In teamfights you delete him and hit his whole team, so group, itemize, and close the game as the bigger threat.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko because you out-range Comet Spear and punish any walk-up without W.","Level 2 stays Neeko's as you control the wave and trade back on his short-range poke.","Level 3 is Neeko's — your E-Q combo out-damages his all-in when you dodge the W stun.","Levels 4-5 remain Neeko's as you kite his engage and out-poke his committed trades.","Level 6 stays Neeko's since your clone-flank Pop Blossom out-bursts him and his R is only a roam threat.","At first item Neeko spikes as your burst overwhelms an AD bruiser with no ranged scaling.","With two-plus items Neeko dominates: a single-target melee who blocks only one angle falls to your AoE."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"qiyana","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Qiyana","Neeko","Qiyana","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Tangle-Barbs online you get a real root, but this is also when Qiyana's E dash plus a charged element (rock near a wall) lets her burst-combo you; hold E to punish her dash-in rather than throwing it first."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom is your equalizer: her Edge of Ixtal needs a wall and telegraphs, so disguise-engage or R her the instant she commits to reset the fight in your favour."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her assassin spike (Hextech Alternator/Youmuu's) lets her one-rotation you; buy an early Seeker's or components and don't sit in brush she can element-charge from."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your AoE Blooming Burst and Pop Blossom outscale her single-target burst in teamfights while she struggles to reach your backline."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove with Q and keep the wave near your tower so her wall/brush plays are weaker","Hold Tangle-Barbs to punish her E dash-in instead of leading with it","Bait or answer her ult with Pop Blossom and disguise picks"],"foe":["Charge rock or brush element next to a wall then E-Q all-in in the 4-5 window","Roam with element speed when you push mindlessly","Land Edge of Ixtal on a stationary Neeko for the full combo"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: you out-range Qiyana's melee element Q and shove Blooming Burst in before she has her E dash to all-in, so poke her off CS and deny her a free element charge.","mid":"Levels 3-5 swing to her once she has E and a charged element near walls, so respect that all-in window and hold Tangle-Barbs; at 6 you flip it back with Pop Blossom, which cleanly beats her wall-dependent, telegraphed ult.","late":"Her first assassin item is her sharpest one-combo threat, so itemize and space it out, but into two items your AoE burst and disguise picks outscale her single-target kit in fights.","whys":["You out-range and out-sustain Qiyana's melee-range element Q at level 1, shoving Blooming Burst before she can trade.","With Q and W speed you clear faster and Qiyana can't all-in without her E dash charged.","Tangle-Barbs gives you the root to punish her whenever she steps into melee to last-hit.","Once she has E plus a charged element near walls, her burst combo out-trades your cooldowns in the 4-5 window.","Pop Blossom's stun and your disguise beat her wall-dependent, telegraphed ult, letting you R her out of the play.","Her assassin item spike lets her one-combo you before your defensive layers come online.","With two items your AoE Q and R and clone control outscale her single-target burst in teamfights."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"ryze","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tangle-Barbs out-ranges Rune Prison, so root Ryze whenever he steps up to CS and follow with Blooming Burst; his mana-hungry Q-E combo keeps him too low to trade back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom is a hard all-in Ryze has no dash to escape; disguise-walk into range and R him, forcing Flash or a kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your burst item spike lands well before his stacking combo scales, so look to solo-kill him or set up your jungler on repeat."},{"when":"Late","text":"Ryze wants teamfight setup and Realm Warp plays; deny them with clone/disguise picks and your AoE stun and you snowball the game."}],"wants":{"you":["Root with Tangle-Barbs the moment he steps to last-hit","All-in at 6 with Pop Blossom since he has no escape dash","Punish his mana costs by forcing repeated short trades"],"foe":["Farm safely under tower and hit item/level power spikes","Land E-Q Rune Prison combos to survive your engages","Use Realm Warp for flanks and objective setups"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-2: Blooming Burst out-pushes Ryze's weak, mana-hungry early Q poke, and W Shapesplitter speed lets you sidestep his E-Q combo and shove him in under tower.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay firmly yours because Tangle-Barbs out-ranges Rune Prison and Ryze has no mobility to answer your root-into-Q burst, and at 6 Pop Blossom gives you a lethal all-in he simply can't escape.","late":"Your first-item burst spike arrives before his stacking combo scales, and into two-plus items you deny his teamfight setup and Realm Warp flanks with disguise picks and AoE stun.","whys":["You win the level-1 push with Blooming Burst while Ryze's early Q poke is weak and drains his mana.","W Shapesplitter speed lets you dodge his E-Q combo and shove him in under tower.","Tangle-Barbs out-ranges Rune Prison, so you root and Q him whenever he steps to CS.","Your waveclear matches his while your poke chunks him harder as his combo mana cost keeps him low.","Pop Blossom is a hard all-in the dash-less Ryze cannot escape, forcing Flash or death.","Your item burst spike bursts him before his stacking combo scales, and he can't survive your R engage.","Ryze needs teamfight setup you deny with clone and disguise picks plus AoE stun."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"swain","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Skill","Skill","Swain"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early you have the edge with Tangle-Barbs, rooting Swain before he lands his own E Nevermove; but as it becomes a dodge check, whiffing your E into his root flips the extended trade thanks to his Q sustain."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both ults are AoE and it's a coinflip around cooldowns: his Demonic Ascension drain versus your Pop Blossom stun comes down to who engages on-form and with summoners up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your burst and his HP/sustain items roughly cancel, so the trade is decided by whether your E lands, not by raw stats; don't feed his passive Soul Fragments."},{"when":"Late","text":"In extended fights and teamfights Swain's R drain and E pull heal him through your burst rotation, so avoid long dances and look to burst-and-reset."}],"wants":{"you":["Force short trades early before his Q bolts and passive sustain ramp","Land Tangle-Barbs first to root him out of his own Nevermove","Burst and disengage rather than fight extended once he has R"],"foe":["Land E Nevermove to root you into his Q bolt combo","Stack Soul Fragments passive off your minions and poke","Drag fights long with R drain and W vision setups"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are yours: you shove first with Blooming Burst and poke Swain before his Q bolts and passive sustain ramp, and W speed lets you sidestep his E Nevermove to win the short trade.","mid":"Levels 4-6 flatten into a skill matchup, a dodge check where landing Tangle-Barbs wins you the trade but whiffing into his Nevermove lets his Q sustain flip it even, and both AoE ults make 6 a cooldown coinflip.","late":"Once he has HP and sustain items his R drain and E pull out-heal your single burst rotation in extended and teamfights, so favour burst-and-reset over long dances.","whys":["You shove first with Blooming Burst and poke Swain before his Q bolts and passive sustain ramp.","W Shapesplitter speed lets you sidestep his E Nevermove and win the short trade while his sustain is low.","Tangle-Barbs lets you root and burst him before he lands his own E root back.","It becomes a dodge check: land your E and you win, whiff into his Nevermove and his Q sustain flips it even.","Both ults are AoE, so his R drain versus your Pop Blossom stun is a cooldown coinflip decided by who engages on-form.","Your burst and his sustain/HP items roughly cancel, leaving the trade to whoever lands their combo.","In extended and teamfights his R drain and E pull out-heal your single burst rotation."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"sylas","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Neeko","Skill","Sylas"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tangle-Barbs lets you root Sylas when he E-dashes in and burst him before Kingslayer heals him, but with both E charges and W sustain up the 4-5 exchanges become a coinflip on who lands their combo first."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Sylas will Hijack your Pop Blossom, so bait it with disguise or a fake commit, then all-in on your terms once his stolen ult is spent or misused."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His sustain items versus your burst roughly even out; the trade hinges on landing E-Q first, so don't dash-chase him into his second E."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Sylas out-bruises you: double-E mobility, Kingslayer sustain, and stolen ults let him win the extended fights your single burst window can't close."}],"wants":{"you":["Root his E-dash engage with Tangle-Barbs and burst before Kingslayer heals","Bait his R Hijack with disguise before committing Pop Blossom","Keep trades short so his W sustain can't grind you out"],"foe":["Hijack your Pop Blossom for a stolen AoE stun","Land Q Chain Lash inner-hit and W Kingslayer to heal through your poke","Drag fights long with double-E mobility and sustain"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 favour you: you control the wave with Blooming Burst and out-range his melee Chain Lash before he has E mobility, and W speed helps you dodge his Q inner-hit.","mid":"Level 4-5 is a skill trade once he has both E charges and W sustain, but 6 tips back to you because even though he Hijacks your Pop Blossom you can bait it with disguise and still win the AoE all-in on your terms.","late":"His first item roughly trades even with yours, but into two-plus items his double-E mobility, Kingslayer sustain, and stolen ults let him out-bruise your single burst window.","whys":["You control the wave with Blooming Burst and out-range his melee Chain Lash before he has E mobility.","W Shapesplitter speed helps you dodge his Q inner-hit and punish his short reach.","Tangle-Barbs roots him when he E-dashes in, letting you burst before Kingslayer heals him.","With both E charges and W sustain it's a skill trade decided by who lands their combo.","You can bait his Hijack with disguise and still win the AoE all-in with Pop Blossom on your terms.","His sustain items versus your burst roughly cancel, so the trade comes down to who lands first.","With two items his double-E mobility, sustain, and stolen ults out-bruise your burst window in extended fights."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"syndra","win":["Syndra","Syndra","Syndra","Syndra","Neeko","Syndra","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Syndra's strongest stretch: her E-Q stun combo and sphere stacking out-poke and threaten a big trade you can't answer at Tangle-Barbs range, so give up CS rather than eat spheres stepping up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom is your one window: disguise-engage past her spheres and stun her before she can E-scatter, punishing her squishy, immobile combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her Luden's/tear spike makes the E-Q-ignite combo lethal before your defensive layers, so hug your side of the lane and buy MR/Seeker's early."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights your AoE R and clone picks outscale her single-target burst once you close the gap, so build to survive one combo and flip the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Concede early CS rather than trade into her sphere poke","Save Pop Blossom to blitz her the moment she wastes E","Build MR and survive one combo to reach your teamfight scaling"],"foe":["Zone you off the wave with Q Dark Sphere and W push","Land E Scatter the Weak on a stunned sphere for the burst combo","Hit her Luden's spike and delete you before your layers"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Syndra: her Q Dark Sphere out-ranges and out-pokes your Blooming Burst, and her E-Q stun threat and W shove zone you off the wave before your Tangle-Barbs range can answer.","mid":"Level 6 is your lifeline, where Pop Blossom lets you disguise-engage past her spheres and stun her squishy combo, but the 4-5 window before it stays hers as sphere stacking keeps you on the back foot.","late":"Her first-item spike keeps her lethal, but into two-plus items your AoE R and clone picks outscale her single-target burst in teamfights once you build to survive her opening combo.","whys":["Her Q Dark Sphere out-ranges and out-pokes your Blooming Burst, chunking you every time you step to CS.","With Q and W she shoves and zones you off the wave while you can't trade back at her range.","Her E-Q stun combo threatens a big trade your shorter Tangle-Barbs range can't answer.","Her sphere stacking and QWE poke keep you on the back foot through the 4-5 window.","Pop Blossom lets you disguise-engage past her spheres and stun her before she can E-scatter.","Her first-item Luden's spike makes the E-Q-ignite combo lethal before your defensive layers come online.","In teamfights your AoE R and clone picks outscale her single-target burst once you close range."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"taliyah","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Taliyah","Skill","Skill","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-trade her early with Tangle-Barbs roots, but once her Q is maxed the worked-ground poke chunks you repeatedly in the 4-5 window, so shove and reset rather than sit in her Q range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Weaver's Wall is a roam tool, not a duel tool; whether she or you gets value comes down to tracking her wall roams and matching macro, so ping and cover."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her poke items and your burst roughly even out; the lane hinges on dodging her Q and W Seismic Shove rather than raw stats."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your AoE all-in and disguise picks outscale her poke in teamfights, and you punish her low mobility with Pop Blossom once you close the gap."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade early before her Q worked-ground poke comes online","Shove and reset through the 4-5 poke window","Track her Weaver's Wall roams and match her macro"],"foe":["Max Q and zone you with worked-ground poke in the 4-5 window","Land W Seismic Shove into E Unraveled Earth for a stun combo","Roam with R Weaver's Wall to snowball other lanes"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are yours: you out-trade Taliyah's early Q before she has worked-ground poke, shoving Blooming Burst in, and W speed dodges her W Seismic Shove setup.","mid":"Level 4-5 swings to her once maxed Q worked-ground poke controls the wave and chunks you, then 6 flattens to a skill window since Weaver's Wall is a roam tool decided by tracking, not a duel you lose in lane.","late":"Her poke items and your burst even out at one item, but into two-plus your AoE all-in and disguise picks outscale her poke and punish her low mobility.","whys":["You out-trade Taliyah's early Q before she has worked-ground poke, shoving with Blooming Burst.","W Shapesplitter speed dodges her W Seismic Shove setup and you win the short exchange.","Tangle-Barbs roots her when she steps up, punishing her before her Q pushes online.","With maxed Q worked-ground poke she chunks you repeatedly and controls the wave in the 4-5 window.","Weaver's Wall is a roam tool, not a duel tool, so value depends on tracking and matched macro.","Her poke items versus your burst even out, so the lane hinges on dodging her Q and W rather than raw stats.","Your AoE all-in and disguise picks outscale her poke and punish her low mobility in teamfights."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"talon","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Talon","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tangle-Barbs roots Talon mid-combo, so when he W-Q gap-closes you root and burst him before his W Rake bleed fully procs; keep the wave shoving to deny his all-in windows."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom's stun beats his Shadow Assault engage; disguise-bait his all-in, then R him as he commits to flip the fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His lethality spike (Youmuu's/Serpent's Fang) lets him one-combo you, especially returning from a roam, so track his pathing and buy an early Seeker's or Zhonya's rush."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your AoE R and clone control outscale his single-target assassination once you itemize HP or Zhonya's, and you punish him in teamfights."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove and deny Talon's W-Q all-in windows","Root his gap-close with Tangle-Barbs and burst before Rake bleeds","Track his roams and answer them with your own tempo"],"foe":["W-Q gap-close for a full Rake bleed combo","Roam with E Assassin's Path and return on a lethality spike","Land R Shadow Assault stealth engage for the reset kill"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: you shove first with Blooming Burst and out-range Talon's melee Rake before he can W-Q all-in, and W speed helps you zone him off CS.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours because Tangle-Barbs roots him mid-combo, your poke keeps him from trading freely, and at 6 Pop Blossom's stun cleanly beats his Shadow Assault engage.","late":"His first lethality item is his one-combo threat, especially post-roam, so track and itemize against it, but into two items your AoE R and clone control outscale his single-target burst.","whys":["You shove first with Blooming Burst and out-range Talon's melee Rake before he can W-Q all-in.","W speed and incoming Tangle-Barbs let you zone him off CS and deny his Q gap-close trade.","Tangle-Barbs roots him mid-combo, letting you burst before his W Rake bleed procs.","You keep priority and match his roams while your poke stops him from all-in trading freely.","Pop Blossom's stun beats his Shadow Assault engage, so you disguise-bait and turn on him.","His lethality spike lets him one-combo you before your defensive layers, especially post-roam.","With two items your AoE R and clone control outscale his single-target assassination once you itemize HP or Zhonya's."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"twistedfate","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With all three abilities you can layer E Tangle-Barbs into Q Blooming Burst on a slowed target; TF has no dash and his only escape is Blue Card's mana or flashing, so a rooted TF eats the full double-Q detonation."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Pop Blossom gives you an all-in TF can't answer up close: charge in under W Shapesplitter movement speed, root with E, and the R stun plus Q burst deletes him before Gold Card matters. His level-6 spike is map pressure (roams/ults), not dueling you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Luden's or Blackfire on Neeko out-trades TF's poke; you have the sustain and the point-and-click threat, while he's stuck kiting a champion who moves faster and roots on E. Shove and deny his Destiny recall-roams."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights your clone plus R backline dive punishes TF hard: he's squishy, immobile, and if he Gold-Cards you he's still in E-Q-R range. You win every extended fight if you reach him."}],"wants":{"you":["Root with E first, then commit Q so it can't be dodged","Track his Destiny (6) and follow or ping his roam target","Use W move speed and clone to bait his Gold Card"],"foe":["Land Gold Card to lock you before you engage","Poke you down with Blue Card and Wild Cards pre-6","Roam with ult and gank sidelanes instead of dueling you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour you: TF's Wild Cards poke is real but you out-sustain it with P heal on minions and your Q clears waves faster, letting you deny his farm without taking a bad trade. He has no way to punish your last-hits without stepping into E range.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are firmly yours: E-Q is a guaranteed burst combo on a champion with zero mobility, and once you hit 6 your R all-in kills him outright. Keep the wave shoved so his only outplay path (Gold Card into a jungler gank or a Destiny roam) is harder to set up.","late":"With items you remain the aggressor: TF is a utility/pick mage who wants to poke and roam, not stand and fight, and your clone-plus-R dive reaches his backline. As long as you don't get caught by a blind Gold Card in fog, extended fights go to you.","whys":["You out-sustain TF's early Wild Cards poke with P minion heals and shove him off farm.","With Q up you clear faster than TF and he can't contest your last-hits without eating E range.","At three abilities your E-into-Q combo bursts an immobile TF who has no dash to dodge it.","Levels 4-5 stay yours because TF still has no escape and your poke plus root out-trades his cards.","Your R Pop Blossom all-in kills TF up close before Gold Card can save him.","One-item Neeko out-trades and out-sustains a squishy TF who only wants to poke and roam.","In 2-item teamfights your clone-plus-R backline dive shreds an immobile, squishy TF."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"veigar","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You have a hard all-in window here before Veigar stacks Baleful Strike into relevance: E Tangle-Barbs roots, Q Blooming Burst bursts, and W move speed closes the gap so you're inside his Event Horizon minimum-cast range where the cage barely matters. Punish every Q he throws to farm by walking him down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Veigar's R Primordial Burst is huge but it's single-target and needs the E cage to land first; if you dodge or sidestep the outer ring of Event Horizon, your R Pop Blossom all-in kills him before he can combo. Bait the W stun with your clone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Race his stacks: a shoving Neeko with Luden's denies Veigar farm and keeps him from the AP threshold where his cage-into-R one-shots. Every wave you crash into tower is stacks he doesn't get."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is the danger zone if you let it get here even — a fed Veigar cage-R deletes squishies. But you dodge with W/clone and flank so you're never the pillar's centre; disrespect the cage and he's a stationary immobile mage you dive."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in levels 3-9 before his AP stacks come online","Shove waves to starve his Baleful Strike stacks","Sidestep the outer ring of E Event Horizon to avoid the stun"],"foe":["Stack Baleful Strike safely to hit his one-shot threshold","Land E cage to guarantee W-Q-R combo","Scale to a late game where cage-R deletes you instantly"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: Veigar is one of the weakest early laners in the game, his Q Baleful Strike is his only tool and you can trade on him freely with E-Q while denying the last-hits that fuel his scaling. Shove and set up your jungler.","mid":"Levels 3-6 heavily favour you and this is your kill window: before Veigar's stacks matter, your E-Q-W burst plus R all-in kills a champion with no mobility and no early defensive tools beyond a single cage. Force the fight now; every trade you win delays his scaling.","late":"With items the matchup theoretically tips toward Veigar's cage-R one-shot, but the lockchart still reads you because you control whether it gets there: keep shoving to starve stacks, dodge Event Horizon with W move speed and clone, and flank so you punish his immobility instead of feeding the pillar.","whys":["You freely out-trade Veigar at level 1 since Baleful Strike is his only tool.","Level 2 stays yours as Veigar has no early combo and you deny his scaling farm.","Your E-Q burst kills a stackless, immobile Veigar in the level 3-5 window.","Levels 4-5 remain your kill window before his AP stacks come online.","Your R all-in kills Veigar if you sidestep Event Horizon's outer ring first.","One-item Neeko keeps shoving to starve stacks and dives an immobile Veigar.","You stay ahead late by dodging the cage with W/clone and flanking his backline immobility."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"vex","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Vex","Vex","Neeko","Vex"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Vex starts controlling the lane here: her passive Doom marks you whenever you dash or move fast, so your W Shapesplitter speed and any engage triggers Shadow Fright, interrupting your E-Q. Respect her Q Mistral Bolt poke and don't feed her passive by moving into it carelessly."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Vex R Shadow Surge is a long-range point-and-click pick that recasts if she gets a kill, and her E-Q-passive combo out-bursts your all-in unless you've saved E to interrupt her R animation. This is her window, not yours; play for waves and jungle proximity rather than a solo fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Luden's back online you flip it: shove the wave and E-Q her before she can set up Doom, and use clone to soak her R Shadow Surge so it wastes on the illusion. Punish her low mobility once your cooldowns are up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vex teamfights are brutal — one R can chain-recast across your squishies and her E fear zones your engage. She out-ranges and out-picks you in the open, so you need clone flanks and to root her before she casts, or she controls the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Save E to interrupt her R Shadow Surge windup","Use clone to bait and soak her R and E fear","Shove and all-in on your item spikes when her Q is down"],"foe":["Trigger passive Doom off your W/dash to interrupt your combo","Poke with Q Mistral Bolt and zone with E Personal Space","Land R Shadow Surge picks and recast for the reset"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour you before Vex's passive matters much: you have the stronger point-blank trade with E-Q and she can't yet punish your aggression, so contest the first waves and deny her free poke. Don't dash needlessly into her Doom mark.","mid":"Levels 3-6 swing to Vex: her Doom passive punishes exactly the mobility your kit wants to use, Shadow Fright interrupts your combos, and at 6 her R Shadow Surge is a safer, longer-range all-in than yours. Play the wave, hold E to interrupt, and avoid trading when her passive is charged.","late":"With items it splits — you claw back a window on your first-item spike by shoving and bursting her when Q is down, but by two items Vex's R chain-picks and E fear zones control teamfights again. Save clone to soak her ult and root her before she casts, or she dictates the fight.","whys":["You out-trade Vex point-blank at level 1 before her Doom passive comes online.","Level 2 stays yours as Vex can't yet punish your E-Q aggression.","At three abilities your burst still beats hers before she sets up the passive reliably.","Levels 4-5 tip to Vex: her Doom passive interrupts the mobility your combo needs.","Vex's level-6 R Shadow Surge is a safer, longer-range all-in than your R.","Your first-item spike lets you shove and burst her when Mistral Bolt is down.","By two items Vex's chain-recast R and E fear zones control fights over your dive."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"viktor","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Viktor","Skill","Neeko","Viktor"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Viktor augments his Q Siphon Power he gets a shield and an empowered auto that wins short trades, and his E Death Ray shoves waves and pokes from range. Your E-Q all-in still threatens him, but he's starting to farm safely under tower and out-range your poke; pick your trade windows when his E is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is roughly even and skill-dependent: your R Pop Blossom all-in can kill him, but Viktor's Chaos Storm is a strong zoning ult and his augmented W Gravity Field roots you out of your combo. Whoever lands their CC first wins — if you E him before he Ws you, you kill; if he Gravity Fields your engage, you die."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike harder on a single item: Luden's/Blackfire Neeko can E-Q-R burst Viktor before his Chaos Storm ramps, and he's immobile with only Gravity Field to peel. Shove and force the all-in while you out-tempo his scaling."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two-item Viktor is a monster: fully augmented, his Chaos Storm plus Gravity Field plus Death Ray zone entire fights and he out-DPSes you in the open. You need clone flanks to reach him and must root before he Ws, or his scaling and zoning take over the game."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in around your first-item spike before Chaos Storm ramps","E-root him before he lands W Gravity Field","Shove waves to deny his safe augment farming"],"foe":["Farm safely and augment Q/W/E to scale","Land W Gravity Field to root you out of your combo","Reach two items where Chaos Storm zones every fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 favour you: before Viktor augments his abilities he's a weak, immobile laner and your E-Q trades beat him cleanly, so contest waves and deny his early farm to slow his augment timings. Push your advantage while he's at his weakest.","mid":"Levels 4-6 tighten up: once Viktor augments Siphon Power and Death Ray he farms safely and out-ranges your poke, and level 6 becomes a coinflip decided by who lands CC first — your E root or his W Gravity Field. Trade only when his E is on cooldown and never walk into a Gravity Field.","late":"Items split the matchup: your first-item spike is a real all-in window where you out-tempo his scaling and burst him before Chaos Storm ramps, but by two items a fully augmented Viktor zones fights with Chaos Storm and Gravity Field and out-DPSes you. Flank with clone and root him first, or his scaling wins.","whys":["Pre-augment Viktor is a weak immobile laner your level-1 E-Q trade beats.","Level 2 stays yours before he augments any ability to farm safely.","At three abilities your burst still cleanly beats an un-augmented Viktor.","Levels 4-5 tip to Viktor once augmented Q and E let him farm safe and out-range you.","Level 6 is even and skill-based: your E root versus his W Gravity Field decides it.","Your first-item spike out-tempos his scaling and bursts him before Chaos Storm ramps.","By two items a fully augmented Viktor zones every fight and out-DPSes your dive."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"vladimir","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is your dominant window: Vladimir is one of the weakest early laners in the game, his Q Transfusion sustain isn't stacked yet and he has no hard escape besides W Sanguine Pool. E-Q him repeatedly, and if you E-root you can burst through his pool timing before he's healthy. Shove and deny his farm to delay his scaling."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even and skill-based: your R Pop Blossom all-in can kill him, but Vlad's W Sanguine Pool untargets him mid-combo and dodges your R stun if he reacts. Bait the pool with your clone or a feint, then commit E-Q-R; if you burn his pool first, he's dead."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You keep the lead on a single item: Neeko's E-Q-R burst still out-paces one-item Vlad's healing, and he's immobile between pools. Force all-ins and set up ganks while his Q sustain can't yet out-heal your damage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vladimir is a hyperscaler, so the game gets harder the longer it goes — but you're favoured in the pick-and-burst pattern: flank with clone, root him with E so Sanguine Pool can't save the whole team, and blow him up before his R Hemoplague amp and drain-tank items take over. Don't let it become a scaling contest."}],"wants":{"you":["Dominate the 3-9 window before Vlad out-heals your burst","Bait W Sanguine Pool with clone before committing R","Shove and deny farm to delay his hyperscaling"],"foe":["Survive lane with Q sustain and W pool to reach items","Use Sanguine Pool to dodge your R and untarget your combo","Scale into a drain-tank that out-heals your burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are firmly yours: Vladimir has a famously weak early game, no ranged poke that beats your E, and only Q Transfusion sustain to survive. Trade aggressively with E-Q, deny his last-hits, and shove so his scaling is delayed and your jungler can punish his immobility.","mid":"Level 5-6 is even and skill-dependent: your all-in threatens him, but W Sanguine Pool can untarget out of your R stun and combo, so the fight hinges on whether you bait the pool first. Keep applying E-Q pressure and force him to burn Q and pool defensively rather than farming freely.","late":"Vladimir hyperscales into a drain-tank, so despite your lane favour the overall matchup is a grind — win it by refusing a scaling contest. Flank with clone, E-root so his pool can't peel the whole team, and burst him before Hemoplague and lifesteal items come fully online; if the game goes very long, his sustain overtakes you.","whys":["Vladimir's famously weak level 1 lets your E-Q trade dominate freely.","Level 2 stays yours as Vlad has only Q sustain and no way to punish you.","At three abilities your E-Q burst beats an immobile, low-sustain Vlad.","Levels 4-5 remain yours before his Transfusion can out-heal your poke.","Level 6 is even and skill-based: whether you bait W Sanguine Pool decides the all-in.","One-item Neeko's E-Q-R burst still out-paces Vlad's early healing.","You stay favoured late by flanking and bursting him before his drain-tank scaling peaks."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"xerath","win":["Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xerath owns this phase: his Q Arcanopulse, W Eye of Destruction and E Shocking Orb out-range everything you have, so he pokes you off the wave and zones your farm with impunity. You can't reach him without W move speed and a flash, and his E stun interrupts any engage. Farm safe, dodge skillshots, and don't take free poke walking up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You start to flip it: R Pop Blossom plus W Shapesplitter speed and clone finally give you the gap-close to punish Xerath's zero mobility. Bait his E Shocking Orb with the clone, then E-root him and all-in — if he whiffs his stun he's dead, because he has no escape whatsoever."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your spike beats his: once you have Luden's and can survive the poke to all-in, an immobile Xerath is easy prey for E-Q-R the moment he's out of position or his E is down. Roam and gank with your speed since he can't follow or peel for himself."},{"when":"Late","text":"Neeko wins the fight if she reaches him: your clone flank plus R dive lands right on top of a stationary artillery mage who dies instantly to your burst. His whole game is landing pokes from max range, so collapse the distance in fights and he has no answer."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the poke phase to your level-6 gap-close spike","Bait E Shocking Orb with clone, then E-root and all-in","Flank with clone and dive his immobile backline in fights"],"foe":["Poke you out of lane with Q/W/E max range pre-6","Land E Shocking Orb to stun your engage","Keep the fight at max range where you can't reach him"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Xerath: he out-ranges your entire kit with Arcanopulse and Eye of Destruction, zones you off farm, and stuns any approach with Shocking Orb. You have no way to trade back through that range, so play safe, minimise the free poke you eat, and just farm to level 6 without dying.","mid":"Level 5-6 is where you take over: R Pop Blossom plus W move speed and clone finally close the gap on a champion with literally no mobility, so bait his E stun with the clone and then E-root into your full burst. Once you can all-in, every whiffed Shocking Orb is a kill.","late":"With items you're the favourite in fights as long as you reach him: an immobile artillery mage folds instantly to a clone flank plus E-Q-R dive, and his only game plan is poking from max range. Collapse the distance, punish his lack of escape, and roam with your speed since he can never follow.","whys":["Xerath out-ranges your whole kit at level 1 and pokes you off the wave.","Level 2 stays his as Eye of Destruction and Q zone your farm freely.","At three abilities his range and E stun keep you from ever trading back.","Levels 4-5 remain Xerath's: you can't close the gap and eat free poke.","At 6 your R plus W speed and clone finally gap-close his zero mobility.","Your first-item spike lets you survive the poke and all-in an immobile Xerath.","Late, your clone flank and R dive delete a stationary artillery mage who can't escape."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"yasuo","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q Blooming Burst and E Tangle-Barbs are cast, not projectiles that his W Wind Wall blocks in the useful way — Q rains down and E is a skillshot you can angle around the wall. Yasuo has to walk up to farm with Q, and when he dashes onto a minion you E-root and Q him for a huge chunk. Punish every time his Wind Wall is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yasuo needs a knockup for his R, and you deny it by fighting alone: without an ally's CC he can only ult off his own Q3 tornado, which you sidestep. Meanwhile your R Pop Blossom stun plus E-Q outright kills him once you've rooted, since he's squishy and his only defence is the windwall and E dashes."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Neeko's Luden's/Blackfire burst beats a one-item Yasuo who has to build toward crit before he's a threat. Shove the wave and all-in when his Wind Wall is on cooldown; a rooted Yasuo can't E-dash out of your combo."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yasuo scales with crit and teamfight knockup-R, so respect his flanks — but your clone plus E-root shuts down his engage, and if you land E on him he can't dash for the duration and eats your full burst. Save E for when he commits R, not before."}],"wants":{"you":["E-root him so he can't E-dash out of your Q burst","All-in when his W Wind Wall is on cooldown","Deny his R by fighting solo with no ally knockup"],"foe":["Block your key cast with W Wind Wall in a trade","Farm safely with Q and stack Flow shield","Scale to crit items and ult off a teammate's CC"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour you: Yasuo has to walk up and last-hit with Q or auto, exposing him to your E-Q trade, and his Wind Wall is on a long cooldown early so you can bait or wait it out. Shove and deny his farm while he's forced to melee-range risk.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours: your E root removes his greatest strength — the E-dash mobility — and locks him for a full Q burst, while Wind Wall only stops one cast and can be angled around. At 6 he can't reliably ult you in a solo fight without his own knockup, so your R all-in wins the duel.","late":"With items you remain favoured in the lane pattern: shove and burst him when Wind Wall is down, and in fights use clone to bait his engage and E-root to cancel his dashes. Respect his crit scaling and flank R, but a rooted Yasuo is a dead Yasuo since he loses all his mobility for the duration.","whys":["Yasuo must walk up to farm at level 1, exposing him to your E-Q trade.","Level 2 stays yours as his Wind Wall is on a long early cooldown to bait out.","Your E root strips his E-dash mobility and locks him for a full Q burst.","Levels 4-5 remain yours: Wind Wall stops only one cast and you angle E around it.","At 6 Yasuo can't reliably ult you solo, so your R all-in wins the duel.","One-item Neeko out-bursts a Yasuo still building toward crit relevance.","Late, a clone bait plus E-root cancels his dashes and deletes him despite crit scaling."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"yone","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have Q Blooming Burst and E Tangle-Barbs together, punish every Yone Q1/Q2 windup: he has to walk into melee to stack Mortal Steel, so root him mid-animation with E and detonate the double Q for a huge chunk before he ever lands the Q3 knockup."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Pop Blossom flips any fight where Yone goes in with E Soul Unbound: bait his spirit-dash, and when his body is stranded you can W into his backline or ult on top of a grouped mid-and-jungle for a guaranteed AoE stun."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Liandry's or Blackfire Torch online your poke Q outranges his all-in threat, so you shove and chunk while his Q stacks and shield decay before he can commit."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights your clone and R stun neuter Yone's R Fate Sealed windup; if he flashes in you can pre-cast R off the knockup and delete him before Fate Sealed lands."}],"wants":{"you":["Root his Q3 knockup windup with E before he can dash back with Spirit Unbound","Shove waves so he can't freeze and force him to eat Q poke last-hitting","Save R Pop Blossom to punish his E return or his R commit"],"foe":["Land Q3 Mortal Steel knockup into his Q burst and W Spirit Cleave shield","Use E Soul Unbound to dodge your Q and Tangle-Barbs then return for a free trade","Roam or all-in with jungle when your clone and R are down"]},"early":"You control levels 1-2 outright: Yone has no reliable poke and must stack Mortal Steel in melee, so bully him off the wave with autos and hold E Tangle-Barbs ready to root any twitch toward CS. Don't waste Q1's inner-ring on the wave you'll want it up to punish his Q windup.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are your window. Yone's only engage is a slow Q3 knockup or an E Soul Unbound that leaves his body behind for 1.5-4s. Root his approach with E, detonate the second half of Blooming Burst for the burst, and back off before his shield ramps. At 6 your R turns any of his all-ins into a punish.","late":"With items your Liandry's/Blackfire poke and clone tricks keep the lead: outshove him, deny the freeze, and in fights hold R Pop Blossom to stun him out of R Fate Sealed. Your AoE and disengage answer his dive better than his sustained damage answers your burst.","whys":["You out-trade and out-range Yone at level 1 since he has no poke and must stack Q in melee.","At level 2 your Q plus early points give you kill pressure he can't match yet.","Level 3 with Q and E lets you root and burst his melee Q windup for a clean advantage.","Through levels 4-5 your E root keeps punishing his slow Q3 and E-return commits.","Your level 6 R Pop Blossom flips his all-ins, so you own the ult timing.","First item your Liandry's poke outranges his engage and snowballs the lane.","Two-plus items your AoE burst and R stun neuter his R Fate Sealed in every fight."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"zed","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Zed","Neeko","Zed","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Zed hits level 4-6 his W Living Shadow gives him double energy and a double-Q poke pattern, so his all-in window opens; respect it by holding E Tangle-Barbs to root him the instant he W-dashes in, and keep your passive clone up so his Q shurikens don't confirm the kill."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 you flip the ult war: when Zed casts R Death Mark on you, immediately pop R Pop Blossom or W Shapesplitter and cross with your clone so the mark's shadow-Q lands on empty air, then E-root and Q-detonate him for the counter-kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Zed's first item (Youmuu's/Serrated) spikes his squishy-kill combo, so this is his strongest window; play back, farm on the edge of the wave, and never step up without E and R available to punish his shadow."},{"when":"Late","text":"With both kits fully online it's skill-based: your AoE clears his shadows in fights and your R stun can catch him mid-R, but a fed Zed can one-shot a positioned-out Neeko, so it comes down to who lands their key cast first."}],"wants":{"you":["Root his W Living Shadow dash-in with E before he stacks Q poke","Cross with clone and W/R to dodge his R Death Mark shadow","Shove the wave so his shadow all-in has less room and he can't freeze"],"foe":["Land double Q shuriken from a W shadow angle to poke you down","Wait for R Death Mark cooldown then all-in a rooted or sidestepped Neeko","Hit his level-4-6 and first-item power spikes before your R is up"]},"early":"You win levels 1-3 clean: Zed's Q Razor Shuriken is easy to sidestep and his energy is too tight to trade repeatedly, so bully him with Q Blooming Burst poke and hold E Tangle-Barbs to root any step-up. Keep your clone alive it makes his shuriken confirm much harder.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are Zed's spike as W Living Shadow and E Shadow Slash come fully online for the double-Q all-in, so respect his energy and don't get caught rooted. But at 6 you take the initiative back: R Pop Blossom and your clone let you dodge R Death Mark, then E-root and detonate Q for the kill.","late":"His first item is his peak all-in threat, so farm safe and only step up with E and R ready. Deep into items it's a skill matchup: your AoE and R stun answer his shadows in fights, but one missed dodge on Death Mark loses the duel, so let him commit first and punish.","whys":["Level 1 you out-poke Zed since his single Q is easy to dodge and his energy is tight.","Level 2 your Q burst and early E pressure beat his thin trade pattern.","Level 3 you still control the lane before his W double-energy all-in exists.","Levels 4-5 favor Zed as W Living Shadow and E enable his double-Q all-in window.","At level 6 you flip it, using R and clone to dodge Death Mark and counter-kill.","First item is Zed's power spike, giving his shadow combo the burst to kill you.","Two-plus items is even skill, decided by who lands their key cast first."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Neeko","Ziggs","Neeko","Neeko","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 is your first real window: with Q Blooming Burst and E Tangle-Barbs you can dash the wave on W Shapesplitter and root him, but from 4-5 his Q Bouncing Bomb and E Hexplosive Minefield out-range and zone you, so pick your angle carefully around his W Satchel knock-back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Pop Blossom is how you close the gap Ziggs builds all game: hold W movement speed and your clone, walk into a bush or fog, then flash-or-W onto him and R for the stun-burst before he can W Satchel himself to safety."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first item your all-in burst outpaces his single-target damage, so a landed E root plus Q plus R deletes him; the whole matchup hinges on you actually reaching him past the minefield."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two-plus items it evens out: he has more waveclear and safer poke, but your roam threat and R pick potential match his scaling, so it becomes a map-tempo game of who converts a pick first."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3, then dash with W and root his step-up with E","Use clone and R Pop Blossom to close distance through fog or a bush","Roam to side lanes since you can't win the ranged poke war straight up"],"foe":["Poke you down with Q Bouncing Bomb and zone CS with E Hexplosive Minefield","W Satchel Charge to knock you out of your E root or all-in range","Shove waves and keep the lane long so his range advantage decides it"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Ziggs: his Q Bouncing Bomb out-ranges everything you have and his Short Fuse passive chunks you at every last-hit, so give ground, farm what you safely can, and don't walk into his E minefield. You simply can't trade into his range yet.","mid":"At 3 you get a window with Q, E and W Shapesplitter to dash-root and burst him, but 4-5 swing back to Ziggs as his minefield and Satchel let him zone and knock you off your all-in. Ball up your angles and use the wave state, don't force a bad step-up into his poke.","late":"Level 6 and your first item are your reclaim points: R Pop Blossom finally gives you the gap-close to punish his lack of escape, so pick from fog and delete him. Deep into items it's even, a tempo fight where your roams and R picks answer his superior waveclear and poke.","whys":["Level 1 Ziggs out-ranges you and his Short Fuse passive punishes every last-hit.","Level 2 his Q poke and zoning still keep you off the wave and behind.","Level 3 you get a Q-E-W dash-root window that lets you punish him for once.","Levels 4-5 swing back as his minefield and Satchel zone and knock you away.","At 6 your R Pop Blossom gap-close finally lets you punish his weak escape.","First item your all-in burst outpaces his single-target poke once you reach him.","Two-plus items evens out into a tempo game of picks versus his waveclear."]},
  {"a":"neeko_mid","b":"zoe","win":["Zoe","Zoe","Neeko","Zoe","Skill","Neeko","Neeko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Level 3 is your punish window: when Zoe steps up to E Sleepy Trouble Bubble the wave, dash with W Shapesplitter and root her with E Tangle-Barbs before her Q Paddle Star can wind up, then detonate Q for a big chunk. From 4-5 she reclaims range, so only commit when her E is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"It's even at 6: your R Pop Blossom can burst her if you already have her rooted, but her R Portal Jump lets her blink out of your ult radius and reposition for a Q, so the fight hinges on whether she wastes Portal Jump before you commit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first item your all-in burst outscales her single-shot poke: a landed E root through your clone plus Q and R deletes her, and she has no reliable escape once Portal Jump is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game strongly favors you; in teamfights your clone bait and R stun let you dodge or eat her E sleep, and once you're on her she folds, while your AoE keeps the fight going after your burst."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 and dodge or bait E Sleepy Trouble Bubble, then W-dash and E-root","Use your clone to soak her E sleep and her charged Q Paddle Star","Force the all-in after her E and R Portal Jump are on cooldown"],"foe":["Land E Sleepy Trouble Bubble then a fully charged Q Paddle Star for a one-shot","Poke you down at max range with Q and W More Sparkles before you close","Keep R Portal Jump up to blink out of your R Pop Blossom radius"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Zoe's: her Q Paddle Star one-shots your health bar from screen range and a landed E sleep into empowered Q can nearly delete you, so hug your minions, dodge the bubble, and never facecheck fog. You can't trade into that range yet.","mid":"At 3 you get a real punish window Q, E and W let you dash-root her E windup and burst before she resets range. Levels 4-5 swing back as she out-spaces you again, and 6 is even because her R Portal Jump can dodge your R Pop Blossom. Commit only when her E and Portal Jump are down.","late":"Your first item flips the matchup for good: your all-in burst outpaces her single-shot poke and she has no escape once Portal Jump is spent. Deep into items you dominate, using clone bait and R stun to eat her sleep and delete her the moment you reach her.","whys":["Level 1 Zoe out-ranges you and a charged Q Paddle Star chunks half your bar.","Level 2 her E sleep into empowered Q threatens a near one-shot you can't answer.","Level 3 your Q-E-W dash-root punishes her E windup for a real advantage.","Levels 4-5 swing back as she reclaims spacing and pokes you with Q.","Level 6 is even since her R Portal Jump can blink out of your R radius.","First item your all-in burst outscales her poke and she has no escape left.","Two-plus items you dominate, dodging her sleep and deleting her on contact."]}
